comment: Number of Unsuccessful Preparations for Relocations with Outgoing HardHandovers (Cell): No radio resources available in target cell Updated: As shown at point A in Figure 1, when receiving a RELOCATION PREPARATION FAILURE message from the CN, the SRNC measures the items listed in Table 1based on different cause values in the best cell that the UE camps on before the hard handover if the relocation is performed with the hard handover_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful Preparations for Relocations with Outgoing HardHandovers (Cell): TRELOCalloc Expiry Updated: As shown at point A in Figure 1, when receiving a RELOCATION PREPARATION FAILURE message from the CN, the SRNC measures the items listed in Table 1based on different cause values in the best cell that the UE camps on before the hard handover if the relocation is performed with the hard handover_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful Preparations for Relocations with Outgoing HardHandovers (Cell): Relocation Failure in Target CN/RNC or Target System Updated: As shown at point A in Figure 1, when receiving a RELOCATION PREPARATION FAILURE message from the CN, the SRNC measures the items listed in Table 1based on different cause values in the best cell that the UE camps on before the hard handover if the relocation is performed with the hard handover_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful Preparations for Relocations with Outgoing HardHandovers (Cell): Relocation not supported in Target RNC or Target system Updated: As shown at point A in Figure 1, when receiving a RELOCATION PREPARATION FAILURE message from the CN, the SRNC measures the items listed in Table 1based on different cause values in the best cell that the UE camps on before the hard handover if the relocation is performed with the hard handover_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful Preparations for Relocations with Outgoing HardHandovers (Cell): Relocation Target not allowed Updated: As shown at point A in Figure 1, when receiving a RELOCATION PREPARATION FAILURE message from the CN, the SRNC measures the items listed in Table 1based on different cause values in the best cell that the UE camps on before the hard handover if the relocation is performed with the hard handover_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful Preparations for Relocations with Outgoing HardHandovers (Cell): O&M Intervention Updated: As shown at point A in Figure 1, when receiving a RELOCATION PREPARATION FAILURE message from the CN, the SRNC measures the items listed in Table 1based on different cause values in the best cell that the UE camps on before the hard handover if the relocation is performed with the hard handover_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful Preparations for Relocations with Outgoing HardHandovers (Cell): No Resource Available Updated: As shown at point A in Figure 1, when receiving a RELOCATION PREPARATION FAILURE message from the CN, the SRNC measures the items listed in Table 1based on different cause values in the best cell that the UE camps on before the hard handover if the relocation is performed with the hard handover_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful Preparations for Relocations with Outgoing HardHandovers (Cell): Unspecified Failure Updated: As shown at point A in Figure 1, when receiving a RELOCATION PREPARATION FAILURE message from the CN, the SRNC measures the items listed in Table 1based on different cause values in the best cell that the UE camps on before the hard handover if the relocation is performed with the hard handover_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Preparations for CS Domain Incoming Inter-RAT Handovers (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of preparations for CS domain incoming inter-RAT handovers_ Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives from the CN a RELOCATION REQUEST message_ In this case, the RNC measures the item in the target cell_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Attempts at CS Domain Outgoing Inter-RAT Handovers (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of attempts at CS domain outgoing inter-RAT handovers_ Updated: The measurement is triggered at point C as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends a UE a HANDOVER FROM UTRAN COMMAND message during the CS domain outgoing inter-RAT handover_ In this case, the RNC measures the item in each cell that the UE camps on_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Attempts at PS Domain Outgoing Inter-RAT Handovers (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of attempts at PS domain outgoing inter-RAT handovers_ Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends the CN a CELL CHANGE ORDER FROM UTRAN message during PS domain inter-RAT outgoing handover_ In this case, the RNC measures the item according to the causes for handovers_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Preparations for CS Domain Outgoing Inter-RAT Handovers (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of preparations for CS domain outgoing inter-RAT handovers_ Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends the CN a RELOCATION REQUIRED message during the CS domain outgoing inter-RAT handover_ In this case, the RNC measures the item in the best cell that the UE camps on_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful Preparations for CS Domain Incoming Inter-RATHandovers for Different Causes (Cell): Traffic Load In The Target Cell Higher Than In The Source Cell Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the TRNC sends a RELOCATION FAILURE message_ In this case, the RNC measures the item according to different causes in the target cell_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful Preparations for CS Domain Incoming Inter-RATHandovers for Different Causes (Cell): Relocation failure in target CN/RNC or target system Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the TRNC sends a RELOCATION FAILURE message_ In this case, the RNC measures the item according to different causes in the target cell_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful Preparations for CS Domain Incoming Inter-RATHandovers for Different Causes (Cell): Relocation not supported in target RNC or target system Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the TRNC sends a RELOCATION FAILURE message_ In this case, the RNC measures the item according to different causes in the target cell_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful Preparations for CS Domain Incoming Inter-RATHandovers for Different Causes (Cell): No resource available Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the TRNC sends a RELOCATION FAILURE message_ In this case, the RNC measures the item according to different causes in the target cell_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful CS Domain Outgoing Inter-RAT Handovers for DifferentCauses (Cell): Configuration Unsupported Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives from a UE a HANDOVER FROM UTRAN FAILURE message during the CS domain inter-RAT outgoing handover_ In this case, the RNC measures the items according to different causes in the best cell that the UE camps on_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful CS Domain Outgoing Inter-RAT Handovers for DifferentCauses (Cell): Physical Channel Failure Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives from a UE a HANDOVER FROM UTRAN FAILURE message during the CS domain inter-RAT outgoing handover_ In this case, the RNC measures the items according to different causes in the best cell that the UE camps on_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful PS Domain Outgoing Inter-RAT Handovers for DifferentCauses (Cell): Configuration Unsupported Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends a CELL CHANGE ORDER FROM UTRAN message and then receives from the UE a CELL CHANGE ORDER FROM UTRAN FAILURE message during the PS domain outgoing inter-RAT handover_ The message indicates that the inter-RAT handover fails_ In this case, the RNC measures the items according to different failure causes_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful PS Domain Outgoing Inter-RAT Handovers for DifferentCauses (Cell): Physical channel failure Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends a CELL CHANGE ORDER FROM UTRAN message and then receives from the UE a CELL CHANGE ORDER FROM UTRAN FAILURE message during the PS domain outgoing inter-RAT handover_ The message indicates that the inter-RAT handover fails_ In this case, the RNC measures the items according to different failure causes_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful Preparations for CS Domain Inter-RAT OutgoingHandovers for Different Causes (Cell): Failure cause: TRELOCalloc expiry Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1_ During an outgoing inter-RAT CS handover, after the RNC sends a RELOCATION REQUIRED message to the CN, the RNC measures the items in the best cell based on the failure causes if the RNC receives a RELOCATION PREPARATION FAILURE message from the CN_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful Preparations for CS Domain Inter-RAT OutgoingHandovers for Different Causes (Cell): Failure cause: Relocation Failure in Target CN/RNC or Target System Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1_ During an outgoing inter-RAT CS handover, after the RNC sends a RELOCATION REQUIRED message to the CN, the RNC measures the items in the best cell based on the failure causes if the RNC receives a RELOCATION PREPARATION FAILURE message from the CN_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful Preparations for CS Domain Inter-RAT OutgoingHandovers for Different Causes (Cell): Failure cause: Relocation not supported in Target RNC or Target system Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1_ During an outgoing inter-RAT CS handover, after the RNC sends a RELOCATION REQUIRED message to the CN, the RNC measures the items in the best cell based on the failure causes if the RNC receives a RELOCATION PREPARATION FAILURE message from the CN_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful Preparations for CS Domain Inter-RAT OutgoingHandovers for Different Causes (Cell): Failure cause: Traffic Load In The Target Cell Higher Than In The Source Cell Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1_ During an outgoing inter-RAT CS handover, after the RNC sends a RELOCATION REQUIRED message to the CN, the RNC measures the items in the best cell based on the failure causes if the RNC receives a RELOCATION PREPARATION FAILURE message from the CN_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful Preparations for CS Domain Inter-RAT OutgoingHandovers for Different Causes (Cell): Failure cause: No Resource Available Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1_ During an outgoing inter-RAT CS handover, after the RNC sends a RELOCATION REQUIRED message to the CN, the RNC measures the items in the best cell based on the failure causes if the RNC receives a RELOCATION PREPARATION FAILURE message from the CN_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful Preparations for CS Domain Inter-RAT OutgoingHandovers for Different Causes (Cell): Failure cause: Unknown Target RNC Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1_ During an outgoing inter-RAT CS handover, after the RNC sends a RELOCATION REQUIRED message to the CN, the RNC measures the items in the best cell based on the failure causes if the RNC receives a RELOCATION PREPARATION FAILURE message from the CN_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful CS Domain Incoming Inter-RAT Handovers (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful CS domain incoming inter-RAT handovers_ Updated: The measurement is triggered at point D as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends the CN a RELOCATION COMPLETE message during the CS domain incoming inter-RAT handover_ In this case, the RNC measures the item in the target cell_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful CS Domain Outgoing Inter-RAT Handovers (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful CS domain outgoing inter-RAT handovers_ Updated: The measurement is triggered at point D as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives an IU RELEASE COMMAND message with the cause of Successful Relocation, Normal Release or Network Optimisation upon sending of a HANDOVER FROM UTRAN COMMAND message during the CS domain outgoing inter-RAT handover_ In this case, the RNC measures the item in the best cell that the UE camps on_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful UE-originated PS Domain Outgoing Inter-RAT Handovers(Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful UE-originated PS domain outgoing inter-RAT handover_ Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives an IU RELEASE COMMAND message with the cause value of Normal Release, Successful Relocation or Network Optimisation_ In this case, the RNC measures the item in each cell that the UE camps on before the relocation_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful RNC-originated PS Domain Outgoing Inter-RAT Handovers(Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful PS domain outgoing inter-RAT handovers originated by the RNC_ Updated: The measurement is triggered at point D as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives an IU RELEASE COMMAND message with the cause value of Successful Relocation, Normal Release or Network Optimisation and sends a RANAP IU RELEASE COMPLETE message during the PS domain outgoing inter-RAT handover_ In this case, the RNC measures the item in the best cell that the UE camps on before the relocation_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful Preparations for CS Domain Outgoing Inter-RAT Handovers(Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful preparations for CS domain outgoing inter-RAT handovers_ Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives from the CN a RELOCATION COMMAND message during the CS domain outgoing inter-RAT handover_ In this case, the RNC measures the item in the best cell that the UE camps on_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of IU RELEASE COMMAND Messages from CS Domain to RNC: This measurement item provides the number of IU RELEASE COMMAND messages that the CS domain sends to the RNC_ The RNC measures this item according to the CN nodes_ The Iu release procedure of the CS domain is a procedure to release the Iu connection and all the UTRAN resources related to the Iu connection_ Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1_ In the RNC-initiated Iu release procedure, when the RNC receives an IU RELEASE COMMAND message from the CS domain, the RNC measures this item_ Figure1 The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 2_ In the CN-initiated Iu release procedure, when the RNC receives an IU RELEASE COMMAND message from the CS domain, the RNC measures this item_ Figure2 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of IU RELEASE COMMAND Messages from PS Domain to RNC: This measurement item provides the number of IU RELEASE COMMAND messages that the PS domain sends to the RNC_ The RNC measures this item according to the CN nodes_ The Iu release procedure of the PS domain is a procedure to release the Iu connection and all the UTRAN resources related to the Iu connection_ Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B, as shown in Figure 1_ In the RNC-initiated Iu release procedure, when the RNC receives an IU RELEASE COMMAND message from the PS domain, it measures this item_ Figure1 The measurement is triggered at point A, as shown in Figure 2_ In the CN-initiated Iu release procedure, when the RNC receives an IU RELEASE COMMAND message from the PS domain, it measures this item_ Figure2 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of IU RELEASE REQUEST Messages from RNC to CS Domain: This measurement item provides the number of IU RELEASE REQUEST messages that the RNC sends to the CS domain_ For the UTRAN causes, the UTRAN requests the CS domain to release the Iu signaling connection for a specified UE by sending the CN an IU RELEASE REQUEST message_ The RNC measures this item according to the CN nodes_ Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A, as shown in Figure 1_ When the RNC sends an IU RELEASE REQUEST message to the CS domain, it measures this item_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of IU RELEASE REQUEST Messages from RNC to PS Domain: This measurement item provides the number of IU RELEASE REQUEST messages that the RNC sends to the PS domain_ The RNC measures this item according to the CN nodes_ For the UTRAN causes, the UTRAN requests the PS domain to release the Iu signaling connection for a specified UE by sending the CN an IU RELEASE REQUEST message_ Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A, as shown in Figure 1_ When the RNC sends an IU RELEASE REQUEST message to the PS domain, it measures this item_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

IP Path Backward Bandwidth Allocated to IP Transport Adjacent Node: This measurement item provides the IP path backward bandwidth allocated to an IP transport adjacent node, that is, the mean backward bandwidth sampled in the measurement period_ Updated: In the measurement period, the RNC automatically takes a sample from the IP path backward bandwidth allocated to an adjacent node of the Iub, Iur or Iu interface_ At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated IP path backward bandwidth by the number of samples to get the mean IP path backward bandwidth allocated to an adjacent node of the Iub, Iur or Iu interface_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

IP Path Forward Bandwidth Allocated to: This measurement item provides the IP path forward bandwidth allocated to an IP transport adjacent node, that is, the mean forward bandwidth sampled in the measurement period_ Updated: In the measurement period, the RNC automatically takes a sample from the IP path forward bandwidth allocated to an adjacent node of the Iub, Iur, or Iu interface_ At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated IP path forward bandwidth by the number of samples to get the mean IP path forward bandwidth allocated to an adjacent node of the Iub, Iur, or Iu interface_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN SUM(os_m3ua_de_unavail_dur) ELSE AVG(os_m3ua_de_unavail_dur) END
comment: Duration of M3UA Destination Entity Unavailability: This measurement item provides the duration during which the M3UA destination entity is unavailable_ Updated: The RNC takes a sample from the status of the M3UA destination entity every 5 seconds_ If the M3UA destination entity is unavailable, this item increases by 5_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Times That M3UA Destination Entity Is Unavailable: This measurement item provides the number of times that the status of M3UA destination entity changes from available to unavailable_ Updated: The RNC measures this item when the last route to a destination entity fails and the destination signaling point becomes unavailable_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of ASPM Messages Received by M3UA Link: This measurement item provides the number of ASPM messages received by the M3UA link_ Updated: The RNC measures this item when the M3UA receives the ASPM messages from the peer end_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of ASPM Messages Transmitted by M3UA Link: This measurement item provides the number of ASPM messages transmitted by the M3UA link_ Updated: The RNC measures this item when the M3UA sends the ASPM messages to the peer end_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN SUM(os_m3ua_lnk_cong_dur) ELSE AVG(os_m3ua_lnk_cong_dur) END
comment: Duration of M3UA Link Congestion: This measurement item provides the duration during which the M3UA link is in congested state_ Updated: The RNC takes a sample from the status of the M3UA link every 5 seconds_ If the link is congested, this item increases by 5_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN SUM(os_m3ua_lnk_fail_dur) ELSE AVG(os_m3ua_lnk_fail_dur) END
comment: Duration of M3UA Link Unavailability: This measurement item provides the duration during which the M3UA link is unavailable_ Updated: The RNC takes a sample from the status of the M3UA link every 5 seconds_ If the link is available, this item increases by 5_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Times That M3UA Link Is Unavailable: This measurement item provides the number of times that the status of M3UA link changes from available to unavailable_ Updated: The RNC measures this item when the status of M3UA link changes from available to unavailable_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of MSU Messages Received by M3UA Link: This measurement item provides the number of MSU messages received by the M3UA link_ Updated: The RNC measures this item when the M3UA link receives from the peer end the messages only including upper layer signaling message_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN SUM(os_m3ua_lnkset_unavail_dur) ELSE AVG(os_m3ua_lnkset_unavail_dur) END
comment: Duration of M3UA Link Set Unavailability: This measurement item provides the duration during which the M3UA link set is unavailable_ Updated: The RNC takes a sample from the status of M3UA link set every 5 seconds_ If the link set is unavailable, this item increases by 5_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Times That M3UA Link Set Is Unavailable: This measurement item provides the number of times that the status of M3UA link set changes from available to unavailable_ Updated: The RNC measures this item when the last available link in the M3UA link set becomes unavailable_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of MSU Messages Transmitted by M3UA Link: This measurement item provides the number of MSU messages transmitted by the M3UA link_ Updated: The RNC measures this item when the M3UA link sends the peer end the messages only including upper layer signaling message_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN SUM(os_mtp3b_dsp_unavail_dur) ELSE AVG(os_mtp3b_dsp_unavail_dur) END
comment: Duration of MTP3B DSP in Inaccessible State: This measurement item provides the duration of an MTP3B DSP in inaccessible state_ Updated: The RNC takes samples from the status of the MTP3B DSP every five seconds_ If the DSP is not accessible, the item increases by 5_ (6810)

Number of MTP3B DSP Changes to Inaccessible State: This measurement item provides the number of MTP3B DSP status changes from the accessible state to inaccessible state_ Updated: The measurement is triggered when the MTP3B DSP is not accessible because the last available route to it is faulty_ (6810)

Number of MTP3B Link Changeovers: This measurement item provides the number of changeovers from one MTP3B link to other MTP3B links for some reason_ Updated: The measurement is triggered in any of the following conditions: the state of one MTP3B link changes from In Service state to Out of Service state, the MTP3B link is operated or maintained by the local end, or the MTP3B link is prohibited by the peer end_ (6810)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN SUM(os_mtp3b_lnk_cong_dur) ELSE AVG(os_mtp3b_lnk_cong_dur) END
comment: Duration of MTP3B Link Congestion: This measurement item provides the duration of MTP3B link congestion_ Updated: The RNC takes samples from the congestion status of the MTP3B link every 5 seconds_ If the link is congested, the item increases by 5_ (6810)

Number of MTP3B Link Congestions: This measurement item provides the number of MTP3B link congestions_ Updated: The measurement is triggered when the MTP3B link in non-congested state receives a congestion indication from the SAAL_ (6810)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN SUM(os_mtp3b_lnk_fail_dur) ELSE AVG(os_mtp3b_lnk_fail_dur) END
comment: Duration of Out-of-Service MTP3B Link: This measurement item provides the duration of the out-of-service MTP3B link_ Updated: The RNC takes samples from the status of the MTP3B link every 5 seconds_ If the link is Out of Service, the item increases by 5_ (6810)

Number of MTP3B Link Failures: This measurement item provides the total number of MTP3B link failures for reasons such as MTP3-B transition from available state to unavailable state and link test failure_ Updated: When the MTP3B link is in service, the measurement is triggered when The MTP3B link receives an Out of Service indication from the SAAL, or The local end deactivates the MTP3B link, or The MTP3B link test fails_ (6810)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN SUM(os_mtp3b_lnk_localinh_dur) ELSE AVG(os_mtp3b_lnk_localinh_dur) END
comment: Duration of Local Inhibition on MTP3B Link: This measurement item provides the duration when the MTP3B link stays locally inhibited after being inhibited at the local end_ Updated: The RNC takes samples from the local management status of the MTP3B link every 5 seconds_ If the link is inhibited, the item increases by 5_ (6810)

Number of Local Inhibitions on MTP3B Link: This measurement item provides the number of inhibitions on the MTP3B link at the local end_ Updated: The measurement is triggered when the local end successfully inhibits the MTP3B link_ (6810)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN SUM(os_mtp3b_lnk_rmtinhibit_dur) ELSE AVG(os_mtp3b_lnk_rmtinhibit_dur) END
comment: Duration of Remote Inhibition on MTP3B Link: This measurement item provides the duration of the MTP3B link in inhibited state after it is successfully inhibited by the remote signaling point_ Updated: The RNC takes samples from the remote management status of the MTP3B link every 5 seconds_ If the link is inhibited, the item increases by 5_ (6810)

Number of Remote Inhibitions on MTP3B Link: This measurement item provides the number of inhibitions on the MTP3B link at the remote signaling point_ Updated: The measurement is triggered when the MTP3B link receives an INH message from the remote signaling point_ (6810)

Number of MSUs Received by MTP3B Link: Number of message signaling units (MSU) received on the MTP3B link_ Updated: The measurement is triggered when the MTP3B link receives any of the following messages from the peer end: signaling network management message, signaling link test message, or upper-layer signaling message_ (6810)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN SUM(os_mtp3b_lnk_service_dur) ELSE AVG(os_mtp3b_lnk_service_dur) END
comment: Service Duration of MTP3B Link: This measurement item provides the service duration of the MTP3B link_ Updated: The RNC takes samples from the status of the MTP3B link every 5 seconds_ If the link is In Service, the item increases by 5_ (6810)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN SUM(os_mtp3b_lnkset_unavail_dur) ELSE AVG(os_mtp3b_lnkset_unavail_dur) END
comment: Duration of MTP3B Link Set in Unavailable State: This measurement item provides the duration (in seconds) of the MTP3B link set in unavailable state_ Updated: The RNC takes samples from system checks the status of the MTP3B link set every five seconds_ If the link set is unavailable, the item increases by 5_ (6810)

Number of MTP3B Link Set Failures: This measurement item provides the number of MTP3B link set failures_ The MTP3B link set fails when it changes from the available state to the unavailable state_ Updated: The measurement is triggered when the last available MTP3B link in the MTP3B link set is faulty_ (6810)

Number of MSU Bytes Received by MTP3B Link: This measurement item provides the number of MSU bytes received by the MTP3B link_ The bytes include signaling information field (SIF) and service information octet (SIO)_ SIF includes upper layer signaling content and routing label_ SIO includes network indicator and service indicator_ Updated: The measurement is triggered when the MTP3B link receives any of following messages: signaling network management message, signaling link test message, or upper-layer signaling message_ (6810)

Number of MSU Bytes Sent by MTP3B Link: This measurement item provides the number of MSU bytes sent by the MTP3B link_ The bytes include signaling information field (SIF) and service information octet (SIO)_ The SIF includes upper layer signaling content and routing label_ The SIO includes network indicator and service indicator_ Updated: The measurement is triggered when the MTP3B link sends any of the following messages to the peer end: signaling network management message, signaling link test message, or upper-layer signaling message_ (6810)

Number of Messages Sent by MTP3B Link: This measurement item provides the number of message signaling units (MSUs) sent by the MTP3B Link_ Updated: The measurement is triggered when the MTP3B link sends any of the following messages to the peer end: signaling network management message, signaling link test message, or upper-layer signaling message_ (6810)

Number of SCCP Connection Release Timeouts: This measurement item provides the number of SCCP connection release timeouts_ Updated: The SCCP starts the release protection timer after sending a connection release message (RLSD)_ It stops the timer when receiving a release response message (RLC) from the peer end_ This measurement is triggered when the SCCP does not receive the release response message from the peer end until the timer expires_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Messages SCCP Sent to Local Subsystem: This measurement item provides the number of messages that the SCCP sends to the local subsystem_ Updated: The measurement is triggered when the SCCP sends a message to the local subsystem_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Messages Handled by SCCP: This measurement item provides the total number of local-end and peer-end messages handled by the SCCP_ Updated: The measurement is triggered when the SCCP sends or receives a message_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of SCCP Message Transmission Failures for Excessive Length: This measurement item provides the number of unsuccessfully transmitted messages because the message size exceeds the maximum capability of the SCCP_ Updated: When the SCCP receives a connectionless message from the RANAP (Radio Access Network Application Part)/RNSAP (Radio Network Subsystem Application Part), the message transmission fails if the message size exceeds the maximum capability (3952 bytes) of the SCCP,_ In this case, the measurement of this item is triggered_ (6810)

Number of NSP-initiated SCCP Connection Releases: This measurement item provides the number of SCCP connection releases initiated by the Network Service Provider (NSP)_ Updated: This measurement is triggered when the SCCP receives a connection release message (RLSD) with the cause of NSP or sends a connection release message (RLSD) with the cause of NSP_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of SCCP Message Reassembly Failures due to Reassembly Timeout: This measurement item provides the number of SCCP message failures due to XUDT/LUDT reassembly timeout_ Updated: The SCCP starts the reassembly timer to wait for subsequent messages when it receives the first segment of an XUDT/LUDT message to be reassemblied_ The SCCP stops the timer when it receives the last segment of the message_ This measurement is triggered when the reassembly timer expires which indicates that the reassembly fails_ (6810)

Number of SCCP Message Reassembly Failures for Lack of Buffer Space: This measurement item provides the number of SCCP XUDT/LUDT message reassembly failures because of insufficient buffer space_ Updated: When the SCCP handles an XUDT/LUDT message to be reassembled and finds that there is no sufficient buffer space, the reassembly fails and the SCCP triggers the measurement of this item_ (6810)

Number of SCCP Message Reassembly Failures for Out of Sequence: This measurement item provides the number of SCCP message reassembly failures because the XUDT/LUDT messages are out of sequence_ Updated: When the SCCP handles an XUDT/LUDT message to be reassembled, it receives a discontinuous segmentation message_ In this case, the reassembly fails and the SCCP triggers the measurement of this item_ (6810)

Number of SCCP Routing Failures Due to DSP Unavailable: This measurement item provides the number of SCCP routing failures because the DSP is not reachable or does not exist_ Updated: This measurement is triggered when the SCCP fails to route messages with the cause of DSP not reachable or DSP not existent_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of SCCP Routing Failures Due to Subsystem Fa: This measurement item provides the number of SCCP routing failures due to subsystem failure_ Updated: The measurement of this item is triggered in either of the following conditions: When routing a message from the local subsystem to the peer subsystem, the SCCP finds that the peer subsystem is unavailable_ When routing a message from the peer subsystem to the local subsystem, the SCCP finds that the local subsystem is unavailable_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of SCCP Routing Failures Due to Subsystem Unequipped: This measurement item provides the number of SCCP routing failures because the subsystem is unequipped_ Updated: The measurement of this item is triggered in either of the following conditions: When routing a message from the local subsystem to the peer subsystem, the SCCP finds that the peer subsystem is unequipped_ When routing a message from the peer subsystem to the local subsystem, the SCCP finds that the local subsystem is unequipped_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of SCCP Routing Failures for Other Causes: This measurement item provides the number of SCCP routing failures for the causes except DSP failure, subsystem failure and subsystem unequipped_ Updated: This measurement is triggered when the SCCP fails to route a message for the causes except DSP failure, subsystem failure or subsystem unequipped_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of CREF Messages Received by SCCP Due to DSP Inaccessible: This measurement item provides the number of connection rejection messages (CREF) received by the SCCP because the DSP is inaccessible_ Updated: This measurement item is triggered when the SCCP receives a connection rejection message with the cause of DSP inaccessible_ (6810)

Number of CREF Messages Received by SCCP Due to DSP Unreachable: This measurement item provides the number of connection rejection messages (CREF) received by the SCCP because the DSP is unreachable_ Updated: This measurement is triggered when the SCCP receives a connection rejection message with the cause of DSP not reachable_ (6810)

Number of CREF Messages Received by SCCP Due to QoS Unavailable: This measurement item provides the number of connection rejection messages (CREF) received by the SCCP because the QoS is unavailable_ Updated: This measurement is triggered when the SCCP receives a connection rejection message (CREF) with the cause of QoS unavailable_ (6810)

Number of Connectionless Messages Received by SCCP: This measurement item provides the number of class 0 and class 1 messages received by the SCCP, that is, the number of connectionless messages received by the SCCP_ SCCP connectionless messages include UDT, XUDT, LUDT, UDTS, XUDTS and LUDTS_ Updated: This measurement is triggered when the SCCP receives a message of class 0 or class 1_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Connection-Oriented Messages Received by SCCP: This measurement item provides the number of class 2 messages received by the SCCP, that is, the number of connection-oriented messages received by the SCCP_ SCCP connection-oriented messages include CR, CC, CREF, RLSD, RLC, DT1 and IT_ Updated: This measurement is triggered when the SCCP receives a message of class 2_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of UDTS Messages Received by SCCP: This measurement item provides the number of UTDS messages received by the SCCP_ Updated: This measurement item is triggered at point B, as shown in Figure 1_ When the SCCP receives a UDTS message, it triggers the measurement of this item_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of SCCP XUDT Segmentation Failures: This measurement item provides the number of SCCP XUDT segmentation failures_ Updated: This measurement is triggered when the size of the connectionless message from the upper layer exceeds the maximum capability of the SCCP (3360 bytes) or when the SCCP fails to request a segmentation reference number_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Messages Handled by SCCP Due to Syntax Errors: This measurement item provides the number of messages discarded by the SCCP because there are syntax errors in the messages_ SCCP syntax errors include protocol type error, calling party address error, called party address error, connection reference number error, and unknown messages_ Updated: This measurement is triggered when the SCCP detects syntax errors in handling local or remote end messages_ (6810)

Number of SCCP Connection Releases due to SCCP Inactivity Test: This measurement item provides the number of connection releases due to SCCP inactivity test_ After the connection is set up, the SCCP starts the inactivity receive timer (TIAR) and inactivity send timer (TIAS)_ The SCCP restarts the TIAS timer each time it sends a connection-oriented message_ If it does not send connection-oriented messages until the TIAS timer expires, the SCCP sends an inactivity test message (IT)_ The SCCP restarts the TIAR timer each time it receives a connection-oriented message (including the IT message)_ If it does not receive connection-oriented messages until the TIAR timer expires, the SCCP releases the connection_ Updated: This measurement is triggered when the SCCP sends a connection release message upon expiry of the TIAR timer_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Connectionless Messages Sent by SCCP: This measurement item provides the number of class 0 and class 1 messages sent by the SCCP, that is, the number of connectionless messages sent by the SCCP_ SCCP connectionless messages include UDT, XUDT, LUDT, UDTS, XUDTS and LUDTS_ Updated: The measurement is triggered when the SCCP sends a message of class 0 or class 1_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Connection-oriented Messages Sent by SCCP: This measurement item provides the number of class 2 messages sent by the SCCP, that is, the number of connection-oriented messages sent by the SCCP_ SCCP connection-oriented messages include CR, CC, CREF, RLSD, RLC, DT1 and IT_ Updated: This measurement is triggered when the SCCP sends a message of class 2_ (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of UDTS Messages Sent by SCCP: This measurement item provides the number of Unit Data Service (UDTS) messages sent by the SCCP_ Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A, as shown in Figure 1_ When the SCCP detects errors in the Unit Data (UDT) message and finds that the protocol type indication is return message on error, the SCCP sends a UDTS message and at this time it triggers the measurement of this item_ Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of RLs Requested to Add on Iub Interface (Cell): The measurement items provide the number of RLs requested to add on the Iub interface in a cell. In this case, the RNC measures the item in the cell where the RLs are requested to establish. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN AVG(vs_amr_ctrl_dl4_75) ELSE SUM(vs_amr_ctrl_dl4_75) END
comment: Mean Number of AMR Speech UEs at Different UL and DL Bit Rates (Cell): Number of UEs that use the CS AMR speech service at the DL bit rate of 4.75 kbit/s in the cell Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample from the number of UEs that use the AMR speech service at the eight different UL and DL rates in the cell. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated number by the number of samples to obtain the mean number of UEs that use the AMR speech service at each bit rate.  (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of DL Rate Decreases for AMR Speech Service (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of decreases of the DL bit rate for the AMR speech service in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A1 as shown in Figure 1, when the AMR speech rate is successfully decreased after the RNC has sent the CN an IU RATE CONTROL message. This message requires the Iu UP in the CN to decrease the DL rate of the AMR speech service. In this case, the RNC measures this item in the best cell that the UE camps on. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Increases of DL Bit Rate for AMR Speech Service (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of increases of the DL bit rate for the AMR speech service in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A1 as shown in Figure 1. When the DL bit rate for the AMR speech service successfully increases after the RNC has sent the CN an IU RATE CONTROL message, the Iu UP of the CN needs to increase the DL bit rate for the AMR speech service. In this case, the RNC measures the item in the best cell that the UE camps on. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN AVG(vs_amr_erlang_bestcell) ELSE SUM(vs_amr_erlang_bestcell) END
comment: Mean Number of AMR Speech UEs in the best cell (Cell): This measurement item provides the mean number of UEs that use the AMR speech service in the best cell. Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample from the number of UEs that use the AMR speech service in the best cell. No matter what kind of AMR service is and which bitrate it takes. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated number by the number of samples to obtain the mean number of UEs that use the AMR speech service in the best cell. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Mean Number of AMR Speech UEs in the best cell (Cell): This measurement item provides the mean number of UEs that use the AMR speech service in the best cell. Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample from the number of UEs that use the AMR speech service in the best cell. No matter what kind of AMR service is and which bitrate it takes. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated number by the number of samples to obtain the mean number of UEs that use the AMR speech service in the best cell. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Signaling PDUs Retransmitted by RLC-AM (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of signaling PDUs retransmitted by the RLC in acknowledged mode. Updated: The RNC measures this item when the signaling PDUs are retransmitted by the RLC in acknowledged mode on the user plane. (6810)

Number of Signaling PDUs Delivered by RLC-AM (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of signaling PDUs delivered by the RLC in acknowledged mode. It doesn't include the PUDs retransmitted. Updated: The RNC measures this item when the downlink signaling PDUs are delivered by the RLC in acknowledged mode on the user plane. (6810)

DL Throughput of CS AMR Service (Cell): This measurement item provides the DL volume of CS AMR service in the best cell. Updated: The RNC measures the total DL volume of CS AMR service by the best cell in the application layer. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

UL Throughput of CS AMR Service (Cell): This measurement item provides the UL volume of CS AMR service in the best cell. Updated: The RNC measures the total UL volume of CS AMR service by the best cell in the application layer. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN AVG(vs_amr_rb_dl_4_75) ELSE SUM(vs_amr_rb_dl_4_75) END
comment: RNC Counter: Mean Number of AMR Speech UEs at Different UL and DL Bit Rates: The measurement items provide the mean number of UEs that use the AMR speech services at different bit rates in both uplink and downlink directions in the RNC. Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample from the number of AMR speech UEs at each of the eight UL and DL bit rates. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated number by the number of samples to obtain the mean number of AMR speech UEs at each rate. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Active IP Connections: This measurement item provides the mean number of active IP connections for an adjacent IP transport node. The RNC calculates the mean number of active IP connections at all sampling points in a measurement period. Updated: In the measurement period, the RNC automatically takes a sample from the number of active IP connections for an adjacent IP transport node. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated number of IP connections by the number of samples to get the mean number of active IP connections for an adjacent node. (6810)

Number of Requests for Resource Allocations by IP Transport Adjacent Node: This measurement item provides the number of requests for resource allocation sent from the radio network layer to the transport layer. Updated: The RNC measures this item when the transport layer receives the requests for resource allocation initiated by the radio network layer. (6810)

Number of IP Connection Setup Requests Received by IP Transport AdjacentNode: This measurement item provides the number of IP connection setup requests from the radio network layer to the transport layer. Updated: The measurement is triggered in either of the following conditions: When an IP cell is established, the radio network layer sends an IP connection setup request to the transport layer. In this case, the RNC measures this item. When a UE establishes services in an IP cell, the radio network layer sends an IP connection setup request to the transport layer. In this case, the RNC measures this item. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful IP Connections for: This measurement item provides the number of successful IP connections established at the transport layer. Updated: The measurement is triggered in either of the following conditions: When an IP cell is established, the radio network layer sends an IP connection setup request to the transport layer. The RNC measures this item when the connection is successfully established. When a UE establishes services in an IP cell, the radio network layer sends an IP connection setup request to the transport layer. The RNC measures this item when the connection is successfully established. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of IP Connection Modifications: This measurement item provides the number of IP connection modification requests from the radio network layer to the transport layer. Updated: The RNC measures this item when the transport layer receives the IP connection modification requests from the radio network layer. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful IP Connection Modifications for IP Transport AdjacentNode: This measurement item provides the number of successful IP connection modifications at the transport layer. Updated: The transport layer receives the IP connection modification requests from the radio network layer. The RNC measures this item when the modification is successful. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of IP Connection Releases: This measurement item provides the number of IP connection release requests from the radio network layer to the transport layer. Updated: The measurement is triggered in either of the following conditions: When an IP cell is released, the radio network layer sends an IP connection release request to the transport layer. The RNC measures this item when the IP connection is successfully released. When a UE releases services in an IP cell, the radio network layer sends an IP connection release request to the transport layer. The RNC measures this item when the IP connection is successfully released. (6810)

Number of Successful Resource Allocations by IP Transport Adjacent Node: This measurement item provides the number of successful resource allocation requests after the transport layer receives resource allocation requests from the radio network layer. Updated: The radio network layer initiates an IP resource allocation request. If the request is successful, the RNC measures this item. (6810)

Number of RB Reconfigurations (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION messages sent by the RNC to the UE in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends a RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION message to the UE. In this case, the RNC measures the item in the best cell that the UE camps on. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of RB Setups (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of RADIO BEARER SETUP messages sent by the RNC to the UE in the best cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends a RADIO BEARER SETUP message to the UE. In this case, the RNC measures the item in the best cell that the UE camps on. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

DL Bit Rate of Iub BCCH Logical Channel (Cell): This measurement item provides the DL data rate of the CRNC (Controlling RNC) on the BCCH logical channel of the Iub interface within the cell in the measurement period, that is, dividing the data transmitted by the transmission time. Updated: The measurement is triggered when the CRNC transmits DL data on the BCCH logical channel of the Iub interface. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

DL Bit Rate of Iub CCCH Logical Channel (Cell): This measurement item provides the DL data rate of CRNC on the CCCH logical channel of the Iub interface within the cell in the measurement period, that is, dividing the data transmitted by the transmission time. Updated: The measurement is triggered when the CRNC transmits DL data on the CCCH logical channel of the Iub interface. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

UL Bit Rate of Iub CCCH Logical Channel (Cell): This measurement item provides the UL data rate of CRNC on the CCCH logical channel of the Iub interface within the cell in the measurement period, that is, dividing the data received by the UL receiving time. Updated: The measurement is triggered when the CRNC receives UL data on the CCCH logical channel of the Iub interface. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN SUM(vs_cellbreath_cpichmin_time) ELSE AVG(vs_cellbreath_cpichmin_time) END
comment: Duration of Max and Min Values of CPICH Power due to Cell Breathing (Cell): Duration of the minimum value of CPICH power due to cell breathing in a cell Updated: When the transmit carrier power (TCP) is greater than the upper threshold configured for cell breathing, the RNC needs to adjust the power of common pilot channel (CPICH). However, if the power of CPICH reaches its maximum value, the CRNC cannot adjust it. The CRNC measures the duration of the maximum values of CPICH power in a measurement period on a cell basis. When the transmit carrier power (TCP) is smaller than the lower threshold configured for cell breathing, the RNC needs to adjust the power of common pilot channel (CPICH). However, if the power of CPICH reaches its minimum value, the CRNC cannot adjust it. The CRNC measures the duration of the minimum values of CPICH power in a measurement period on a cell basis. If the cell breathing algorithm switch is disabled in the measurement period, the values of the two items are zero. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN SUM(vs_cellbreath_cpichmax_time) ELSE AVG(vs_cellbreath_cpichmax_time) END
comment: Duration of Max and Min Values of CPICH Power due to Cell Breathing (Cell): Duration of the maximum value of CPICH power due to cell breathing in a cell Updated: When the transmit carrier power (TCP) is greater than the upper threshold configured for cell breathing, the RNC needs to adjust the power of common pilot channel (CPICH). However, if the power of CPICH reaches its maximum value, the CRNC cannot adjust it. The CRNC measures the duration of the maximum values of CPICH power in a measurement period on a cell basis. When the transmit carrier power (TCP) is smaller than the lower threshold configured for cell breathing, the RNC needs to adjust the power of common pilot channel (CPICH). However, if the power of CPICH reaches its minimum value, the CRNC cannot adjust it. The CRNC measures the duration of the minimum values of CPICH power in a measurement period on a cell basis. If the cell breathing algorithm switch is disabled in the measurement period, the values of the two items are zero. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of CPICH Power Adjustments due to Cell Breathing (Cell): Number of CPICH power increases due to cell breathing in a cell Updated: When the TCP is greater than the upper threshold configured for cell breathing, the RNC needs to adjust the power of common pilot channel (CPICH). The CRNC measures the number of CPICH power increases in a measurement period on a cell basis. When the TCP is smaller than the lower threshold configured for cell breathing, the RNC needs to adjust the power of common pilot channel (CPICH). The CRNC measures the number of CPICH power decreases in a measurement period on a cell basis. If the cell breathing algorithm switch is disabled in the measurement period, the values of the two items are zero. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of CPICH Power Adjustments due to Cell Breathing (Cell): Number of CPICH power decreases due to cell breathing in a cell Updated: When the TCP is greater than the upper threshold configured for cell breathing, the RNC needs to adjust the power of common pilot channel (CPICH). The CRNC measures the number of CPICH power increases in a measurement period on a cell basis. When the TCP is smaller than the lower threshold configured for cell breathing, the RNC needs to adjust the power of common pilot channel (CPICH). The CRNC measures the number of CPICH power decreases in a measurement period on a cell basis. If the cell breathing algorithm switch is disabled in the measurement period, the values of the two items are zero. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN AVG(vs_csload_erlang_equiv_plmn_rnc) ELSE SUM(vs_csload_erlang_equiv_plmn_rnc) END
comment: RNC Counter: Equivalent Erlang of CS Domain of RNC for each Operator: This measurement item provides the equivalent Erlang values of all services in the CS domain of the RNC for each Operator. The item is measured only when the RAN sharing function is switched on. Updated: The RNC periodically takes the samples of the equivalent Erlang values of all services in the CS domain for each Operator. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC calculates the mean sample (divide the accumulated value by the sampling times). Each time a CS domain service is admitted, the RNC converts its rate to the equivalent Erlang, and then increases the equivalent Erlang of the CS domain of the RNC. Each time a CS domain service is released, the RNC decreases the equivalent Erlang of the CS domain of the RNC. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN AVG(vs_csload_erlang_equiv_rnc) ELSE SUM(vs_csload_erlang_equiv_rnc) END
comment: RNC Counter: Equivalent Erlang of CS Domain in RNC: This measurement item provides the equivalent Erlang values of all the services in the CS domain in the RNC. Updated: The RNC periodically takes the samples from the equivalent Erlang values of all the services in the CS domain. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated equivalent Erlang values by the number of samples to obtain the mean equivalent Erlang values of all the services in the CS domain. Each time a CS domain service is established, the RNC converts its rate to the equivalent Erlang, and then increases the equivalent Erlang of the CS domain in the current RNC. Each time a CS domain service is released, the RNC converts its rate to the equivalent Erlang and decreases the equivalent Erlang of the CS domain in the current RNC. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful DCH Reconfigurations to Decrease DL Bit Rate (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful dynamic configurations to decrease the DL bit rate of the PS BE service. The channel handover here refers to a handover between DCHs. An RNC can initiate a dynamic channel configuration procedure by the RB reconfiguration or transport channel reconfiguration. Updated: Take the RB reconfiguration procedure as an example. The RNC sends a RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION message to the UE, notifying the UE to reduce the DL bit rate. If the RNC finds that the DL bandwidth of the UE decreases after receiving the RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE, at point A1 as shown in Figure 1, the RNC measures the item in the best cell that the UE camps on. Figure1 (6810)

Number of Successful DCH Reconfigurations to Increase DL Bit Rate (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful dynamic configurations to increase the DL bit rate of the PS BE service. Percentage of GCU CPU Usage over Alarm Threshold: This measurement item provides the percentage of the time when the CPU usage of the GCU/GCG subsystem exceeds the alarm threshold to the time of the whole measurement period. The item indicates how the CPU load is over the alarm threshold. Updated: Samples are taken every second in the specified measurement period. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Maximum Usage of GCU: This measurement item provides the maximum usage of GCU/GCG message packets in the specified measurement period. The item indicates the usage of message packets in the measurement period. Updated: Samples are taken every second in the specified measurement period. (6810)

Mean Usage of GCU Message Packets: This measurement item provides the mean usage of GCU/GCG message packets in the specified measurement period. The item indicates the usage of message packets in the measurement period. Updated: Samples are taken every second in the specified measurement period. (6810)

Number of Bytes of MBMS Services Received by GTP-U: This measurement item provides the number of GTP-U PDU bytes of MBMS services received by the RNC. Updated: This measurement is triggered when the RNC receives a message of MBMS service from the peer GTP-U. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Bytes of Background Services Received by GTP-U: This measurement item provides the number of GTP-U PDU bytes of PS background services received by the RNC. Updated: This measurement is triggered when the RNC receives a message of background service from the peer GTP-U. (6810)

Number of Bytes of Background Services Sent by GTP-U: This measurement item provides the number of GTP-U PDU bytes of PS background services sent by the RNC. Updated: This measurement is triggered when the RNC sends a message of background service to the peer GTP-U. (6810)

Number of Bytes of Conversational Services Received by GTP-U: This measurement item provides the number of GTP-U PDU bytes of PS conversational services received by the RNC. Updated: This measurement is triggered when the RNC receives a message of conversational service from the peer GTP-U. (6810)

Number of Bytes of Conversational Services Sent by GTP-U: This measurement item provides the number of GTP-U PDU bytes of PS conversational services sent by the RNC. Updated: This measurement is triggered when the RNC sends a message of PS conversational service to the peer GTP-U. (6810)

Number of Bytes of Interactive Services Received by GTP-U: This measurement item provides the number of GTP-U PDU bytes of PS interactive services received by the RNC. Updated: This measurement is triggered when the RNC receives a message of interactive service from the peer GTP-U. (6810)

Number of Bytes of Interactive Services Sent by GTP-U: This measurement item provides the number of GTP-U PDU bytes of PS interactive services sent by the RNC. Updated: This measurement is triggered when the RNC sends a message of interactive service to the peer GTP-U. (6810)

Number of Bytes of Streaming Services Received by GTP-U: This measurement item provides the number of GTP-U PDU bytes of PS streaming services received by the RNC. Updated: This measurement is triggered when the RNC receives a message of streaming service from the peer GTP-U. (6810)

Number of Bytes of Streaming Services Sent by GTP-U: This measurement item provides the number of GTP-U PDU bytes of PS streaming services sent by the RNC. Updated: This measurement is triggered when the RNC sends a message of PS streaming service to the peer GTP-U. (6810)

Number of Bytes Received by GTP-U: This measurement item provides the number of GTP-U PDU bytes received by the RNC. Updated: This measurement is triggered when the RNC receives a message from the peer GTP-U. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Bytes Sent by GTP-U: This measurement item provides the number of GTP-U PDU bytes sent by the RNC. Updated: This measurement is triggered when the RNC sends a message to the peer GTP-U. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Received Packets Discarded by GTP-U: This measurement item provides the number of received packets discarded by the GTP-U because GTP-U buffer is full. Updated: The measurement is triggered when the GTP-U discards a packet received from the peer end. (6810)

Number of To-Be-Sent Packets Discarded by GTP-U: This measurement item provides the number of to-be-sent packets discarded by the GTP-U because GTP-U buffer is full. Updated: The measurement is triggered when the GTP-U discards packet to be sent to the peer end. (6810)

Number of Packets Received by GTP-U: This measurement item provides the number of packets received by the GTP-U. Updated: The measurement is triggered when the GTP-U receives a packet from the peer end. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Packets Transmitted by GTP-U: This measurement item provides the number of packets transmitted by the GTP-U. Updated: The measurement is triggered when the GTP-U sends a packet to the peer end. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Blind Handover Attempts (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of blind handover attempts on a per cell basis. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC decides to perform a blind inter-frequency hard handover. In this case, the RNC measures the item in the best cell that the UE camps on. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Outgoing Inter-Frequency Hard Handovers due to DL QoS inCompressed Mode (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of outgoing inter-frequency hard handovers due to DL QoS in compressed mode. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC decides to perform an outgoing inter-frequency hard handover in compressed mode. In this case, the RNC measures the item in the source cell. Figure1 (6810)

Number of Decisions for Incoming Hard Handovers (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of decisions for incoming hard handovers for a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends a reconfigure message to the UE. In this case, the RNC measures the item in the target cell. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Outgoing Inter-Frequency Hard Handover Requests due to LoadBalance (Cell): There is only one cell before handover Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION or a RADIO BEARER RELEASE message to the UE after triggering a hard handover procedure due to load balance. In this case, the RNC measures the item in the best cell that the UE camps on before the hard handover, as shown below. Figure1  (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Outgoing Inter-Frequency Hard Handover Requests due to LoadBalance (Cell): There are more than one radio links before handover Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION or a RADIO BEARER RELEASE message to the UE after triggering a hard handover procedure due to load balance. In this case, the RNC measures the item in the best cell that the UE camps on before the hard handover, as shown below. Figure1  (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of Intra-Frequency Hard Handover Requests: This measurement item provides the number of intra-frequency hard handover requests initiated by the RNC. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B, as shown in Figure 1. To initiate an intra-frequency hard handover procedure, the RNC first sends a RADIO LINK SETUP REQUEST message to the NodeB. After it receives a RADIO LIN SETUP RESPONSE message, the RNC sends a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION message to the UE. At this moment, the measurement of this item is triggered. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Hard Handover Attempts Between Neighboring Cells: This measurement item provides the number of hard handover attempts between neighboring cells. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B, as shown in Figure 1. During the hard handover procedure, for example, when the RNC sends a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message to the UE, the cells that the UE camps on before the hard handover are source cells and the one that the UE camps on after the hard handover is the target cell. In this case, the RNC should measure this item for each pair of source and target cells. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Requests for Outgoing Inter-Frequency Hard Handovers BetweenDifferent NodeBs of RNC (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of requests for outgoing inter-frequency hard handovers between different NodeBs of the same RNC in a cell. In this case, the source cell and the target cell belong to the same RNC but different NodeBs. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION or a RADIO BEARER RELEASE message to a UE, and the source cell and the target cell belong to the same RNC but different NodeBs. In this case, the RNC measures the items in each source cell that belongs to the NodeBs different from the target cells before the hard handover. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Requests for Outgoing Intra-Frequency Hard Handovers betweenDifferent NodeBs of RNC (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of requests for outgoing intra-frequency hard handovers between different NodeBs of the same RNC in a cell. In this case, the source cell and the target cell belong to the same RNC but different NodeBs. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC sends a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION, TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION, RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION, or RADIO BEARER RELEASE message to a UE after it decides to perform a hard handover, the RNC measures the item in the source cell if the source cell and the target cell belong to the same RNC but different NodeBs. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Relocations with Outgoing Inter-Frequency Hard Handovers (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of relocations with outgoing inter-frequency hard handovers in a cell. After successful preparation for relocations with inter-frequency hard handovers, the SRNC originates a reconfiguration procedure for the UE. The reconfiguration procedure involves the following messages: RADIO BEARER SETUP, RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION, RADIO BEARER RELEASE, TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION, and PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION. Here, the source cell and the target cell belong to different RNCs. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the SRNC sends, for example, a RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION message to the UE during the SRNC relocation with an inter-frequency hard handover. In this case, the RNC measures the item in the SRNC cell that the UE camps on. If the SRNC sends a RADIO BEARER SETUP message, a RADIO BEARER RELEASE message, a TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message or a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message to the UE, the RNC also measures the number of reconfigurations for SRNC relocations with inter-frequency hard handovers. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Requests for Outgoing Inter-Frequency Hard Handovers Between RNCs(Cell): This measurement item provides the number of requests for outgoing inter-frequency hard handovers between RNCs in a cell. In this case, the source cell and the target cell belong to different RNCs, and the inter-frequency hard handover is performed through the Iur interface. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION or a RADIO BEARER RELEASE message to a UE, and the source cell and the target cell belong to different RNCs. In this case, the RNC measures the items in the best cell that the UE camps on before the hard handover. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Reconfigurations for Relocations with Outgoing Intra-FrequencyHard Handovers (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of reconfigurations for relocations with outgoing Intra-Frequency hard handovers in a cell. After successful preparation for relocation with intra-frequency hard handover, the SRNC originates a reconfiguration procedure for the UE. The reconfiguration procedure involves the following messages: RADIO BEARER SETUP, RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION, RADIO BEARER RELEASE, TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION, and PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION. In this case, the source cell and the target cell belong to different RNCs. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the SRNC sends the message, for example, a RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION message to the UE during the SRNC relocation with intra-frequency hard handover. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Requests for Outgoing Intra-Frequency Hard Handovers Between RNCs(Cell): This measurement item provides the number of requests for outgoing intra-frequency hard handovers between RNCs in a cell. In this case, the source cell and the target cell belong to different RNCs, and the intra-frequency hard handover is performed through the Iur interface. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION or a RADIO BEARER RELEASE message to a UE after it decides to perform a hard handover. If the source cell and the target cell belong to different RNCs, the RNC measures the item in the best cell that the UE camps on before the hard handover. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Requests for Outgoing Inter-Frequency Hard Handovers in NodeB(Cell): This measurement item provides the number of requests for outgoing inter-frequency hard handovers in the NodeB in a cell. The inter-frequency hard handover in the NodeB means that the source cell and the target cell of the hard handover belong to the same NodeB. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION or a RADIO BEARER RELEASE message to the UE, and the source cell and the target cell belong to the same NodeB but have different frequencies. In this case, the RNC measures the item in each source cell that belongs to the same NodeB of the target cell before the hard handover. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Requests for Outgoing Intra-Frequency Hard Handovers in NodeB(Cell): This measurement item provides the number of requests for outgoing intra-frequency hard handovers in the NodeB in a cell. In this case, the source cell and the target cell belong to the same NodeB. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC sends a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION, TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION, RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION, or RADIO BEARER RELEASE message to a UE after it decides to perform a hard handover. If both the source cell and the target cell belong to the same NodeB, the RNC measures the item in the source cell. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of Hard Handover Requests: This measurement item provides the number of hard handover requests initiated by the RNC. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B, as shown in Figure 1. To initiate a hard handover procedure, the RNC first sends a RADIO LINK SETUP REQUEST or a RADIO LINK ADDITION REQUEST message to the NodeB. After the RNC receives a RADIO LIN SETUP RESPONSE or a RADIO LINK ADDITION RESPONSE message, it sends a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION message to the UE. At this moment, the measurement of this item is triggered. Figure1 (6810)

Number of Decisions for Incoming Inter-Frequency Hard Handovers inCompressed Mode (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of decisions for incoming inter-frequency hard handovers triggered by the RNC in compressed mode. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC decides an incoming inter-frequency hard handover in compressed mode. In this case, the RNC measures the item in the target cell. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Decisions for Outgoing Inter-Frequency Hard Handovers inCompressed Mode (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of decisions for outgoing inter-frequency hard handovers triggered by the RNC in compressed mode. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC decides an outgoing inter-frequency hard handover in compressed mode. In this case, the RNC measures the item in the best cell of the UE. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Decisions for Incoming Hard Handovers (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of decisions for incoming hard handovers in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives a MEASUREMENT REPORT message from a UE and decides an incoming hard handover. In this case, the RNC measures the item in the target cell. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Decisions for Outgoing Hard Handovers (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of decisions for outgoing hard handovers in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives a MEASUREMENT REPORT from a UE and decides an outgoing hard handover. In this case, the RNC measures the item in the best cell of the UE. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of Hard Handover Requests Initiated by the RNC: This measurement item provides the number of hard handover requests initiated by the RNC. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A, as shown in Figure 1. After receiving a measurement report from a UE, the RNC measures this item if it decides to initiate a hard handover. The procedure shown in Figure 1 is performed only when the RNC sends a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message to the UE. Figure1 (6810)

Number of Unsuccessful Outgoing Inter-Frequency Hard Handovers due to LoadBalance (No Response) (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of unsuccessful outgoing inter-frequency hard handovers due to load balance with the failure cause of no response. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message, or a TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message, or a RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or a RADIO BEARER RELEASE COMPLETE message from the UE after triggering a hard handover procedure due to load balance, and starts the timer to wait for response from the UE. If the RNC fails to receive response upon expiry of the time, it measures the item in the best cell that the UE camps on before the hard handover. Figure1 (6810)

Number of Unsuccessful Hard Handovers Between Neighboring Cells Due to NoResponse from UE: This measurement item provides the number of unsuccessful hard handovers between neighboring cells due to no response from the UE. Updated: During a hard handover, for example, when the RNC sends a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message to the UE, the RNC starts the timer and receives no response from the UE until the timer expires. The RNC measures this item for each pair of source and target cells. Here, the source cells refer to the cells that the UE camps on before the hard handover. The target cells refer to the cells that the UE camps on after the hard handover. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsuccessful Outgoing Intra-Frequency Hard Handovers Between RNCs(Cell): Configuration unsupported Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION FAILURE, or a TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION FAILURE message, or a RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE, or a RADIO BEARER RELEASE FAILURE message from a UE during an intra-frequency hard handover. Number of Unsuccessful Outgoing Hard Handovers for Different Causes (Cell): RL addition failure Updated: As shown in Figure 1, if the RNC fails to perform the hard handover before sending a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION or a RADIO BEARER RELEASE message to the UE, it measures the item for different failure causes in the cell that the UE camps on. Figure1 (6810)

Number of Requests for Outgoing Inter-Frequency Hard Handovers (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of requests for outgoing inter-frequency hard handovers initiated by the RNC Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC decides to add an RL for inter-frequency hard handover and sends a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION or a RADIO BEARER RELEASE message to the UE.
