Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B, as shown in Figure 1. To initiate an inter-frequency hard handover procedure, the RNC first sends a RADIO LINK SETUP REQUEST message to the NodeB. After it receives a RADIO LIN SETUP RESPONSE message, the RNC sends a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION message to the UE. At this moment, the measurement of this item is triggered. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of Call Drops due to Inter-Frequency Hard Handover Failure: This measurement item provides the number of call drops due to inter-frequency hard handover failure in the RNC. Updated: The measurement is trigger at point A, as shown in Figure 1. During inter-frequency hard handover, the RNC sends a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION message to the UE and starts a timer to wait for the response from the UE. If the UE returns a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION FAILURE message, or a TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION FAILURE message, or a RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE message, it indicates that the hard handover fails. If the RNC cannot maintain the call connected before the hard handover, it initiates an RRC connection release procedure, which results in call drops. At this moment, the measurement of this item is triggered. Figure1 The measurement is triggered at point A, as shown in Figure 2. During inter-frequency hard handover, the RNC sends a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION message to the UE and then starts a timer to wait for a response from the UE. If the RNC does not receive the response from the UE until the timer expires, it indicates that the hard handover fails. If the RNC cannot maintain the call connected before the hard handover, it initiates an RRC connection release procedure, which results in call drops. At this moment, the measurement of this item is triggered. Figure2 (6810)

In this case, the RNC measures the item in the target cell of the UE in the inter-frequency hard handover procedure. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful Incoming Inter-Frequency Hard Handovers (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful incoming inter-frequency hard handovers initiated by the RNC. In this case, the RNC measures the items in the best cell that the UE camps on before the hard handover. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful Relocations with Outgoing Intra-Frequency HardHandovers (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful relocations with outgoing intra-frequency hard handovers in a cell. The item is measured in the SRNC cell where the UE locates. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of Successful Hard Handovers: This measurement item provides the number of successful hard handovers initiated by the RNC. When the RNC decides to initiate a hard handover, it sends a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message, or a RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION message to the UE. If the RNC receives a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message, TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message, or RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE, it indicates that the hard handover is successful. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point C, as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC receives a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE, or a TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message, or a RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from a UE during hard handover, the measurement of this item is triggered. Figure1 (6810)

When the RNC sends a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message or a TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message to the UE, the RNC measures this item in the original serving cell on condition that the serving cell is changed and the target cell is in the DRNC. Number of Unsuccessful HSDPA MAC-d Flow Deletions (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of unsuccessful HSDPA MAC-d flow deletions in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at either of the following two points: At point B as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives from the NodeB a RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION FAILURE message or the guard timer expires after the RNC sends the RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION PREPARE message, the RNC measures the item in the cell if the HSDPA MAC-d flow fails to be deleted. Figure1 At point A as shown in Figure 2, when the RNC sends a RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION CANCEL message to NodeB after receiving a RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION READY message, it measures this item in the cell of the RL. Figure2 (6810)

Number of Unsuccessful MAC-d Flow Setups (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of unsuccessful MAC-d flow setups in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at either of the following two points: At point B as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives from the NodeB a RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION FAILURE message, when the timer waiting for acknowledgement messages expires after the RNC sends the RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION PREPARE message, or when the RNC sends a RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION CANCEL to the NodeB, the RNC measures the item in the cell if the RL is reconfigured for HSDPA service. During the RL reconfiguration, if the RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION PREPARE message contains an IE HS-DSCH MAC-d flows To Add or HSDSCH FDD Information, it indicates that the RL is set up for HSDPA service. Figure1 At point B as shown in Figure 2, when the RNC receives from the NodeB a RADIO LINK SETUP FAILURE message or the guard timer expires after the RNC sends the RADIO LINK SETUP REQUEST message, the RNC measures the item in the cell if the RL is set up for HSDPA service. During the RL setup, if the RADIO LINK SETUP REQUEST message contains an IE HSDSCH FDD Information, it indicates that the RL is set up for HSDPA service. Figure2 (6810)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN AVG(vs_hsdpa_macd_mean_cell) ELSE SUM(vs_hsdpa_macd_mean_cell) END
comment: Mean Number of MAC-d Flows (Cell): This measurement item provides the mean number of MAC-d flows in a cell. Updated: In an HSDPA service cell, the system periodically takes a sample of the number of MAC-D flows. At the end of the measurement period, the accumulated value of the data at all sampling points is divided by the number of samples to obtain the mean number of MAC-d flows in the measurement period. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Released MAC-d Flows (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of released MAC-d flows in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at either of the following two points: At point C as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends a RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION COMMIT message to the NodeB to delete the MAC-d flow of the HSDPA service, the RNC measures this item in an HSDPA cell that the UE camps on. This item does not take the reconfiguration during the change of serving cells into consideration. Figure1 At point B as shown in Figure 2, the RNC sends a RADIO LINK DELETION REQUEST message to the NodeB to delete an RL bearing the HSDPA service and waits for the response. When the RNC receives a RADIO LINK DELETION RESPONSE message from the NodeB or fails to receive the response within a specified period, it measures this item in an HSDPA cell that the UE camps on. Figure2 (6810)

Number of Successful HSDPA MAC-d Flow Deletions (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful HSDPA MAC-d flow deletions in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at either of the following two points: At point C as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends a RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION COMMIT message to the NodeB, and if the serving cell is changed or the HSDPA MAC-d flow is deleted, the RNC measures this item in the cell of the RL. Figure1 At point B as shown in Figure 2, during the deletion of the radio link of the HSDPA serving cell, when the RNC sends a RADIO LINK DELETION REQUEST message to the NodeB, the RNC measures this item in the cell of the RL if the RNC receives a RADIO LINK DELETION RESPONSE message from the NodeB. Figure2 (6810)

Number of Successful MAC-d Flow Setups (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful MAC-d flow setups in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point C as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC sends a RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION COMMIT message to the NodeB, the RNC measures this item in the cell of the RL. During the RL reconfiguration, if the RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION PREPARE message contains an IE HS-DSCH MAC-d flows To Add, it indicates that the RL is set up for HSDPA service. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Mean Downlink Throughput of MAC-d Flow (Cell): This measurement item provides the mean downlink throughput of MAC-d flow in a cell. Updated: When data is transmitted in an HSDPA cell, the RNC measures the total data transfer time of the UE and the total number of bits in the received data in the cell. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the total number of bits by the total data transfer time to obtain the mean downlink throughput of MAC-d flow in the cell. The RLC header overhead and the retransfer data are excluded. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Transmitted Downlink Bytes in MAC-d Flow (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of bytes in the transmitted downlink data in the MAC-d flow in a cell. Updated: When data is transmitted in an HSDPA cell, the RNC measures the total number of bytes in the transmitted downlink data at the RLC layer for the MAC-d flow in the cell. The RLC header overheand and the retransfer data are excluded. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Mean Downlink Throughput of MAC-d Flow of Copper BE Traffic (Cell): This measurement item provides the mean downlink throughput of MAC-d flow of copper BE traffic in a cell. Updated: When data of copper BE traffic is transmitted in an HSDPA serving cell, the RNC measures the total data transfer time of the UE and the total number of bits in the transmitted data at the RLC layer in the HSDPA serving cell. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the total number of bits by the total data transfer time to obtain the mean downlink throughput at the RLC layer for the MAC-d flows of copper BE traffic. The RLC header overhead and the retransfer data are excluded. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Downlink Bytes Transmitted in MAC-d Flow of Copper BE Traffic(Cell): This measurement item provides the number of downlink bytes transmitted in the MAC-d flow of copper BE traffic in a cell. Updated: When data of copper BE traffic is transmitted in an HSDPA serving cell, the RNC measures the total number of bytes transmitted in the MAC-d flow of the RLC layer. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Mean Downlink Throughput of MAC-d Flow of Golden BE Traffic (Cell): This measurement item provides the mean downlink throughput of MAC-d flow of golden BE traffic in a cell. Updated: When data of golden BE traffic is transmitted in an HSDPA serving cell, the RNC measures the total data transfer time of the UE and the total number of bits in the transmitted data at the RLC layer in the HSDPA serving cell. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the total number of bits by the total data transfer time of the UE to obtain the mean downlink throughput of MAC-d flows at the RLC layer for the golden BE traffic. The RLC header overhead and the retransfer data are excluded. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Downlink Bytes Transmitted in MAC-d Flow of Golden BE Traffic(Cell): This measurement item provides the number of bytes in the transmitted downlink data in the MAC-d flow of golden BE traffic in a cell. Updated: When data of golden BE traffic is transmitted in an HSDPA serving cell, the RNC measures the total number of bytes transmitted in the MAC-d flow of the RLC layer. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Downlink Traffic of HSDPA PS Domain of RNC for each Operator: This measurement item provides the downlink traffic of all the HSDPA services in the PS domain of the RNC for each Operator. The item is measured only when the RAN sharing function is switched on. Updated: The RNC periodically takes the samples of the downlink traffic values (in kbit/s) of all the HSDPA services in the PS domain for each Operator. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC calculates the mean sample (divide the accumulated value by the sampling times). The downlink traffic of all the HSDPA services in the PS domain refers to the traffic measured at the RLC layer. The data does not include the RLC head data. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: DL Traffic of HSDPA PS Domain in RNC: This measurement item provides the downlink traffic of all the HSDPA services in the PS domain within the RNC. Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample from the downlink traffic values of all the HSDPA services in the PS domain. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated traffic values by the number of samples to obtain the mean downlink traffic of all the HSDPA services in the PS domain. The downlink traffic of all the HSDPA services in the PS domain refers to the traffic measured at the RLC layer. The data does not include the RLC head data. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Maximum Downlink Traffic of HSDPA PS Domain of RNC for each Operator: This measurement item provides the maximum downlink traffic of all the HSDPA services in the PS domain of the RNC for each Operator. The item is measured only when the RAN sharing function is switched on. Updated: The RNC periodically takes the samples of the downlink traffic values (in kbit/s) of all the HSDPA services in the PS domain for each Operator. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC calculates the maximum sample value. The downlink traffic of all the HSDPA services in the PS domain refers to the traffic measured at the RLC layer. The data does not include the head data of RLC. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Maximum DL Traffic of HSDPA PS Domain in RNC: This measurement item provides the maximum downlink traffic of all the HSDPA services in the PS domain within the RNC. Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample from the downlink traffic values of all the HSDPA services in the PS domain. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC calculates the maximum downlink traffic of all the HSDPA services in PS domain within the RNC. The downlink traffic of all HSDPA services in the PS domain refers to the traffic obtained at the RLC layer. The data does not include the RLC head data. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Normally Released HSDPA Services (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of normally released HSDPA services in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives the IU RELEASE COMMAND message, the RNC releases related RABs and sends the IU RELEASE COMPLETE message to the CN. If the IU RELEASE COMMAND message is initiated by the CN, or if the RNC sends an IU RELEASE REQUEST message to the CN due to User Inactivity before the CN initiates the IU RELEASE COMMAND message, or if the UE initiates a signaling connection release, the RNC releases the corresponding RAB bearing the HSDPA service and measures this item in an HSDPA cell that the UE camps on. Figure1 The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 2, when the RNC receives the RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message where there are RABs to be released, the RNC releases related RABs and sends the RAB ASSIGNMENT RESPONSE message to the CN. If the RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message is initiated by the CN, or if the RNC sends RAB RELEASE REQUEST message to the CN due to User Inactivity before the CN initiates the RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message, or if the UE initiates a signaling connection release, the RNC releases the corresponding RAB bearing the HSDPA service and measures this item in an HSDPA cell that the UE camps on. Figure2 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Attempts to Change HS-DSCH Serving Cells: This measurement item provides the number of attempts to change HS-DSCH serving cells. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A, as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC sends the UE a PHYSICAL CHANNLE RECONFIGRATION message indicating that the serving cell changes, the RNC measures this item for each pair of source and target cells. Here, source cells refer to the serving cells before change and target cells refer to the serving cells after change. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful Changes of HS-DSCH Serving Cells: This measurement item provides the number of successful changes of HS-DSCH serving cells. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B, as shown in Figure 1. Number of Attempts to Change Serving Cells (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of attempts to change serving cells. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. When sending a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message or a TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message to a UE, the RNC measures this item in the original serving cell if the serving cell changes or if the RNC sends an ACTIVE SET UPDATE message to the UE to change the serving cell. This item is used to measure changes of serving cells in soft handover procedure instead of hard handover procedure. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful Changes of Serving Cells (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful changes of serving cells. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1. This item is used to measure changes of serving cells in soft handover procedure instead of hard handover procedure. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN AVG(vs_hsdpa_ue_mean_cell) ELSE SUM(vs_hsdpa_ue_mean_cell) END
comment: Mean Number of HSDPA UEs in a Cell: This measurement item provides the mean number of HSDPA UEs in a serving cell. The value of this unit is lower than or equal to that of the VS.CellDCHUEs measurement. Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample from the number of HSDPA UEs in the cell. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated number of UEs by the number of samples to obtain the mean number of HSDPA UEs in the measurement period. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Mean Uplink Throughput of Mac-d flows of Copper BE Traffic (Cell): This measurement item provides the mean UL throughput of MAC-d flow of copper BE traffic in a cell. Updated: When data of copper BE traffic is received in an HSUPA serving cell, the RNC measures the period of time when the UE is online and the number of received bytes of the RLC layer in the HSUPA serving cell. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the total bits by the time to obtain the mean UL throughput of MAC-d flow of copper BE traffic. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Bytes Receive in Mac-d flow of Copper BE Traffic (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of bytes received by the MAC-d flow of copper BE traffic in a cell. Updated: When data of copper BE traffic is received in an HSUPA serving cell, the RNC measures the total number of bytes received in the MAC-d flow of the RLC layer. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Updated: This measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC sends an ACTIVE SET UPDATE message to the UE and an EDCH link is added or deleted for the soft handover, the RNC measures this item in the cell where the EDCH link is added or deleted. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful Attempts to Add or Delete EDCH Links due to SoftHandover (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful attempts to add or delete the EDCH link in a cell due to the soft handover. Updated: This measurement is triggered at point C as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC receives an ACTIVE SET UPDATE CMP message from the UE and an EDCH link is added or deleted during the soft handover, the RNC measures this item in the cell where the EDCH link is added or deleted. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Mean Uplink Throughput of Mac-d flows of Golden BE Traffic (Cell): This measurement item provides the mean UL throughput of MAC-d flow of golden BE traffic in a cell. Updated: When data of golden BE traffic is received in an HSUPA serving cell, the RNC measures the data transfer time of the UE and the total number of bits in the received uplink data at the RLC layer in the HSUPA serving cell. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the total number of bits by the data transfer time of the UE to obtain the mean UL throughput of MAC-d flow of golden BE traffic in the cell. The RLC header overhead and the retransfer data are excluded. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Bytes Receive in Mac-d flow of Golden BE Traffic (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of bytes received by the MAC-d flow of golden BE traffic in a cell. Updated: When data of golden BE traffic is received in an HSUPA serving cell, the RNC measures the total number of bytes received in the MAC-d flow of the RLC layer. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of EDCH MACD FLOW Unsuccessfully Deleted: This measurement item provides the number of failures to delete EDCH MACD FLOW in a cell. Updated: This measurement is triggered at point B shown in Figure 1. When the RNC receives a RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION FAILURE message from the NodeB, or when it receives no response from the NodeB before timeout, and the HSUPA RABs are deleted, the RNC measures this item in the cell where the radio link exists. Figure1 This measurement is triggered at point A shown in Figure 2, when the RNC sends a RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION CANCEL message to the NodeB and the HSUPA RABs are deleted, the RNC measures this item in the cell where the radio link exists. During the reconfiguration of the radio link, the HSUPA RABs are deleted if the RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION PREPARE message contains EDCH Mac-d flows To Delete. Figure2 (6810)

Number of EDCH MACD FLOW Unsuccessfully Set Up: This measurement item provides the number of failures of the RNC to set up EDCH MACD FLOW in a cell. Updated: This measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC receives a RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION FAILURE message from the NodeB, or when the timer expires after the RNC sends the RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION PREPARE message, if the RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION PREPARE message is used to setup HSUPA RABs, the RNC measures this item in the cell where the radio link exists. During the reconfiguration of the radio link, the HSUPA RABs are set up if the message RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION PREPARE contains the newly added EDCH MACD FLOW. Figure1 This measurement is triggered at point B shown in Figure 2, when the RNC sends a RADIO LINK SETUP REQUEST message to the NodeB. If the RNC receives a RADIO LINK SETUP FAILURE message from the NodeB, or if the timer set to wait for the response message from the NodeB expires, the RNC measures this item in the cell where the radio link exists. During the setup of the radio link, the HSUPA RABs are set up if the RADIO LINK SETUP REQUEST message contains the EDCH FDD Information. Figure2 This measurement is triggered at point B shown in Figure 3, when the RNC sends a RADIO LINK ADDITION REQUEST message to the NodeB. If the RNC receives a RADIO LINK ADDITION FAILURE message from the NodeB, or if the timer set to wait for the response message from the NodeB expires, the RNC measures this item in the cell where the radio link exists. During the addition of the radio link, the HSUPA RABs are added if the RADIO LINK ADDITION REQUEST message contains the EDCH FDD Information. Figure3 (6810)

Number of EDCH MACD FLOW Successfully Deleted: This measurement item provides the number of successful attempts to delete EDCH MACD FLOW from a UE in a cell. Updated: This measurement is triggered at point C shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends a RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION COMMIT message to the NodeB and the HSUPA RABs are deleted, the RNC measures this item in the cell where the radio link exists. During the reconfiguration of the radio link, the HSUPA RABs are deleted if the RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION PREPARE message contains EDCH Mac-d flows To Delete. Figure1 This measurement is triggered at point A shown in Figure 2. When the RNC sends a RADIO LINK DELETION REQUEST message to the NodeB to delete the radio link for the HSUPA service, the RNC measures this item in the cell where the radio link exists. Figure2 (6810)

Number of EDCH MACD FLOW Successfully Set Up: This measurement item provides the number of successful attempts of the RNC to set up the EDCH MACD FLOW in a cell. Updated: This measurement is triggered at point C as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends a RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION COMMIT message to the NodeB. If the HSUPA RABs are set up, the RNC measures this item in the cell where the radio link exists. During the reconfiguration of the radio link, the HSUPA RABs are set up if the message RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION PREPARE contains the newly added EDCH MACD FLOW. Figure1 This measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 2, when the RNC sends a RADIO LINK SETUP REQUEST/RADIO LINK ADD REQUEST message to the NodeB. If the RNC receives a RADIO LINK SETUP RSP/RADIO LINK ADD RSP message from the NodeB or if the RNC receives a RADIO LINK SETUP FAIL/RADIO LINK ADD FAIL message from the NodeB, the RNC measures this item in the cell where the radio link is successfully set up for the HSUPA service. During the setup of the radio link, the radio link for the HSUPA cell will be established if the RADIO LINK SETUP REQUEST/RADIO LINK ADD REQUEST message contains the EDCH FDD Information. Figure2 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Mean Uplink Throughput of Mac-d flows (Cell): This measurement item provides the mean UL throughput of MAC-d flow in a cell. Updated: When data is received in an HSUPA active cell, the RNC measures the actual data transfer time of the UE and the number of bits in the received data. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the total number of bits by the actual data transfer time of the UE to obtain the mean UL throughput of the RLC layer for the MAC-d flow in the cell. The RLC header overhead and the retransfer data are excluded. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Bytes in Received Uplink Data at the RLC Layer of Mac-d flow(Cell): This measurement item provides the total number of bytes in the received uplink data at the RLC layer for all the MAC-d flows in a cell. Updated: When data is received in an HSUPA active cell, the RNC measures the total number of bytes in the received uplink data at the RLC layer for the MAC-d flow in the cell. The RLC header overhead and the retransfer data are excluded. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Maximum Uplink Traffic of HSUPA PS Domain of RNC for each Operator: This measurement item provides the maximum uplink traffic of all the HSUPA services in the PS domain of the RNC for each Operator. The item is measured only when the RAN sharing function is switched on. Updated: The RNC periodically takes the samples of the uplink traffic values (in kbit/s) of all the HSUPA services in the PS domain for each Operator. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC calculates the maximum sample value. The uplink traffic of all the HSUPA services in the PS domain refers to the traffic measured at the RLC layer. The data does not include the head data of RLC. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Maximum UL Traffic of HSUPA PS Domain in RNC: This measurement item provides the maximum uplink traffic of all the HSUPA services in the PS domain within the RNC. Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample from the uplink traffic values of all the HSUPA services in the PS domain. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC calculates the maximum uplink traffic of all the HSUPA services in the PS domain within the RNC. The uplink traffic of all the HSUPA services in the PS domain refers to the traffic obtained at the RLC layer. The data does not include the RLC head data. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Uplink Traffic of HSUPA PS Domain of RNC for each Operator: This measurement item provides the uplink traffic of all the HSUPA services in the PS domain of the RNC for each Operator. The item is measured only when the RAN sharing function is switched on. Updated: The RNC periodically takes the samples of the uplink traffic values (in kbit/s) of all the HSUPA services in the PS domain for each Operator. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC calculates the mean sample (divide the accumulated value by the sampling times). The uplink traffic of all the HSUPA services in the PS domain refers to the traffic measured at the RLC layer. The data does not include the RLC head data. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: UL Traffic of HSUPA PS Domain in RNC: This measurement item provides the uplink traffic of all the HSUPA services in the PS domain within the RNC. Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample from the uplink traffic values of all the HSUPA services in the PS domain. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated values by the number of samples to obtain the mean uplink traffic of all the HSUPA services in the PS domain. The uplink traffic of all the HSUPA services in the PS domain refers to the traffic obtained at the RLC layer. The data does not include the RLC head data. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of HSUPA RAB Establishment Attempts of BE Service for Copper-LevelUsers (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of HSUPA RAB establishment attempts of BE service for copper-level users in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. When receiving a RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message from the SGSN, the RNC measures this item in the serving cell of the HSUPA service if the service is set up for copper-level users. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of HSUPA RAB Establishment Attempts of BE Service for Golden-LevelUsers (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of HSUPA RAB establishment attempts of BE service for golden-level users in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. When receiving a RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message from the SGSN, the RNC measures this item in the serving cell of the HSUPA service if the service is set up for golden-level users. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of HSUPA RAB Establishment Attempts of BE Service for Silver-LevelUsers (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of HSUPA RAB establishment attempts of BE service for silver-level users in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. When receiving a RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message from the SGSN, the RNC measures this item in the serving cell of the HSUPA service if the service is set up for silver-level users. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Attempts to Set Up HSUPA RABs (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of attempts to set up HSUPA RABs in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC receives a RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message from the SGSN, and if the RNC decides that the message the HSUPA RABs, it measures this item in the HSUPA serving cell. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of HSUPA RABs Abnormally Released by RNC: This measurement item provides the number of HSUPA RABs abnormally released by the RNC in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. When there is an abnormal case after the RAB setup, the RNC sends an IU RELEASE REQUEST message to the CN. The CN then sends an IU RELEASE COMMAND message to the RNC. Then, the RNC releases the RAB and responds with an IU RELEASE COMPLETE message, if the RAB is set up for the HSUPA service and not released for Successful Relocation, Normal Release, User Inactive, Network Optimis, or Ue Generated Sig Conn Rel, the RNC measures this item in the HSUPA cell that the UE camps on. Figure1 The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 2. When there is an abnormal case after the RAB setup, the RNC sends an RAB RELEASE REQUEST message to the CN. The CN then sends an RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message to the RNC. Then, the RNC releases the RAB and responds with an RAB ASSIGNMENT RESPONSE message, if the RAB is set up for the HSUPA service and not released for Successful Relocation, Normal Release, User Inactive, Network Optimis, or Ue Generated Sig Conn Rel, the RNC measures the items in the HSUPA cell that the UE camps on. Figure2 The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 3. When there is an abnormal case after the RAB setup, the RNC sends an RAB RELEASE REQUEST message to the CN. The CN then sends an IU RELEASE REQUEST message to the RNC. Then, the RNC releases the RAB and responds with an IU RELEASE COMPLETE message, if the RAB is set up for the HSUPA service and not released for Successful Relocation, Normal Release, User Inactive, Network Optimis, or Ue Generated Sig Conn Rel, the RNC measures the items in the HSUPA cell that the UE camps on. Figure3 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of HSUPA RABs Normally Released: This measurement item provides the number of HSUPA RABs normally released in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives the IU RELEASE COMMAND message, the RNC releases related RABs and sends the IU RELEASE COMPLETE message to the CN. If the IU RELEASE COMMAND message is initiated by the CN, or if the RNC sends an IU RELEASE REQUEST message to the CN due to User Inactivity before the CN initiates the IU RELEASE COMMAND message, or if the UE initiates a signaling connection release, the RNC releases the corresponding RAB bearing the HSUPA service and measures this item in this HSUPA serving cell. Figure1 The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 2, when the RNC receives the RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message where there are RABs to be released, the RNC releases related RABs and sends the RAB ASSIGNMENT RESPONSE message to the CN. If the RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message is initiated by the CN, or if the RNC sends RAB RELEASE REQUEST message to the CN due to User Inactivity before the CN initiates the RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message, or if the UE initiates a signaling connection release, the RNC releases the corresponding RAB bearing the HSUPA service and measures this item in this HSUPA serving cell. Figure2 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of HSUPA RABs Released by RNC for Release of UE Signaling Connection: This measurement item provides the number of HSUPA RABs released by the RNC for the release of the UE signaling connection. Updated: This measurement is triggered at point A shown in Figure 1. When the RABs are set up and the UE sends a SIGNALLING CONNECTION RELEASE INDICATION message to the RNC, the RNC sends an IU RELEASE REQUEST message to the CN and releases corresponding RABs after receiving an IU RELEASE COMMAND message from the CN. Then, it sends the IU RELEASE COMPLETE message to the CN. If the RABs to be released are HSUPA RABs, the RNC measures this item in the HSUPA serving cell. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful HSUPA RAB Establishments of BE Service for Copper-LevelUsers (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful HSDPA RAB establishments of BE service for copper-level users in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1. After receiving a RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE message from a UE, the RNC sends a RAB ASSIGNMENT RESPONSE message to the SGSN. If the assignment is for setting up the HSUPA service, the RNC measures this item in the serving cell of the HSUPA service. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful HSUPA RAB Establishments of BE Service for Golden-LevelUsers (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful HSUPA RAB establishments of BE service for golden-level users in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1. After receiving a RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE message from a UE, the RNC sends a RAB ASSIGNMENT RESPONSE message to the SGSN. If the assignment is for setting up the HSUPA service, the RNC measures this item in the serving cell of the HSUPA service. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful HSUPA RAB Establishments of BE Service for Silver-LevelUsers (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful HSUPA RAB establishments of BE service for silver-level users in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1. After receiving a RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE message from a UE, the RNC sends a RAB ASSIGNMENT RESPONSE message to the SGSN. If the assignment is for setting up the HSUPA service, the RNC measures this item in the serving cell of the HSUPA service. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful Attempts to Set Up HSUPA RABs (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful attempts to set up the HSUPA RABs in a cell. Updated: This measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives a RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE message from the UE and sends a RAB ASSIGNMENT RESPONSE message to the SGSN. If the assignment is for establishing the HSUPA RABs, the RNC measures this item in the serving cell where the HSUPA RABs are set up. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Attempts to Change EDCH Serving Cells due to Soft Handover orMultiple Links (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of attempts to change the EDCH serving cells because the soft handover is performed or multiple links exist. Updated: This measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message to the UE. If the HSUPA serving cell changes, the RNC measures this item in the original HSUPA serving cell. This item is used to indicate the change of HSUPA serving cells in the soft handover state instead of the hard handover state. Figure1 This measurement triggered at point B as shown in Figure 2, when the RNC sends an ACTIVE SET UPDATE message to the UE. If the HSUPA serving cell changes during the soft handover, the RNC measures this item in the original HSUPA serving cell. Figure2 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Attempts to Change EDCH Serving Links due to Soft Handover orMultiple Links Between RNCs: This measurement item provides the number of attempts to change EDCH serving links due to soft handover or multiple links between RNCs. It is mearued in the original serving cell. Updated: This measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC sends a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message or a TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message to the UE, the item is measured in the original serving cell on condition that the serving cell is changed and the target cell is in the DRNC. This item only indicates the situation that the serving cell is changed in the soft handover. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful Attempts to Change EDCH Serving Cells due to SoftHandover or Multiple Links (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful attempts to change the EDCH serving cells because the soft handover is performed or multiple links exist. Updated: This measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECFG COMPLETE message from the UE. If the HSUPA serving cell changes, the RNC measures this item in the original HSUPA serving cell. The item is used to indicate the change of HSUPA serving cells in the soft handover state instead of the hard handover state. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful Attempts to Change EDCH Serving Links due to SoftHandover or Multiple Links Between RNCs: This measurement item provides the number of successful attempts to change EDCH serving links due to soft handover or multiple links between RNCs. It is mearued in the original serving cell. Updated: This measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC recives a PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECFG COMPLETE message or a TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECFG COMPLETE message from the UE, the RNC measures the item in the original serving cell on condition that the serving cell is changed and the target cell is in the DRNC. This item only indicates the situation that the serving cell is changed in the SHO. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Mean Uplink Throughput of Mac-d flows of Silver BE Traffic (Cell): This measurement item provides the mean UL throughput of MAC-d flow of silver BE traffic in a cell. Updated: When data of silver BE traffic is received in an HSUPA serving cell, the RNC measures the period of time when the UE is online and the number of received bytes of the RLC layer in the HSUPA serving cell. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the total bits by the time to obtain the mean UL throughput of MAC-d flow of silver BE traffic. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Bytes Receive in Mac-d flow of Silver BE Traffic (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of bytes received by the MAC-d flow of silver BE traffic in a cell. Updated: When data of silver BE traffic is received in an HSUPA serving cell, the RNC measures the total number of bytes received in the MAC-d flow of the RLC layer. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN AVG(vs_hsupa_ue_mean_cell) ELSE SUM(vs_hsupa_ue_mean_cell) END
comment: UTRAN 6810 : Mean Number of HSUPA: This measurement item provides the mean number of HSUPA UEs in a cell, which is measured in E-DCH active set. The measurement does not contain the HSUPA UEs under the DRNC. Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample from the number of HSUPA UEs in the cell. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated number of UEs by the number of samples to obtain the mean number of HSUPA UEs in the measurement period. UTRAN 6900 : Enlarge the measurement range of the counter. Originally this counter only counts the users in SRNC, not in DRNC. Now users in both SRNC and DRNC will be counted. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

The item indicates the maximum rate received by the IMA GROUP. Updated: Samples are taken every five seconds in the specified measurement period. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Peak Transmit Rate of IMA GROUP: This measurement item provides the peak transmit rate of the IMA GROUP in the specified measurement period. Mean Delay Jitter of RTP Packets Received over a Single IP Path: This measurement item provides the mean delay jitter of RTP packets received over a single IP path. Updated: When IP transport is applied to the Iu interface and RTCP is supported, each time an RTP packet is received in the downlink, the delay jitter of the packet is calculated on the basis of the local time when the packet is received and the value of Ts in the packet. Then, the mean delay jitter can be calculated according to the following formula: Mean delay jitter of received RTP packets = Sum of delay jitter of received RTP packets /Total times (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Mean RTT of Packets Received over a Single IP Path: This measurement item provides the Round Trip Time (RTT) of packets received over a single IP path. Updated: When IP transport is applied to the Iu interface and RTCP is supported, after an RTCP packet is transmitted from the local end, RTT of the received RTCP packet can be calculated each time an RTCP packet with Reception Report Block is received in the downlink. The RTT is calculated on the basis of the time of transmitting that RTCP packet, the time of receiving this RTCP packet, and the DLSR field of the received RTCP packet. The formula is as follows: RTT = the time of receiving this RTCP packet - the time of transmitting that RTCP packet - DLSR in the received RTCP packet. Then, the mean RTT is calculated as follows: Mean RTT = Sum of RTT/ Total times. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Local Received Bandwidth of a Single IP Path: This measurement item provides the local received bandwidth of a single IP path during a specified measurement period. Updated: When IP transport is applied to the Iu interface and RTCP is supported, the local received bandwidth of a single IP path during a specified measurement period can be calculated according to the following formula: Local received bandwidth = total amount of RTP data in KB received over the IP path/length of the measurement period (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Local Transmitted Bandwidth of a Single IP Path: This measurement item provides the local transmitted bandwidth of a single IP path during a specified measurement period. Updated: When IP transport is applied to the Iu interface and RTCP is supported, the local transmitted bandwidth of a single IP path during a specified measurement period can be calculated according to the following formula: Local transmitted bandwidth = total amount of RTP data in KB transmitted over the IP path/length of the measurement period (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Total Amount of RTP Data in KB Received over a Single IP Path: This measurement item provides the total amount of RTP data in kilobytes received over a single IP path during a specified measurement period. Updated: When IP transport is applied to the Iu interface and RTCP is supported, this measurement item is increased by the size of the RTP packet payload in kilobytes each time the Iu UP receives a downlink data packet during a specified measurement period. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Total Amount of RTP Data in KB Transmitted over a Single IP Path: This measurement item provides the total amount of RTP data in kilobytes transmitted over a single IP path during a specified measurement period. Updated: When IP transport is applied to the Iu interface and RTCP is supported, this measurement item is incremented by the size of the RTP packet payload in kilobytes each time the Iu UP transmits an uplink user data packet or an in-band signaling packet during a specified measurement period. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Ratio of Duration of RTP Delay Jitter Exceeding Threshold to Total ActiveDuration: This measurement item provides the ratio of the time during which the RTP delay jitter exceeds the threshold to the total time during which an IP path is active. This measurement is specific to the single IP path during a specified measurement period. Updated: When IP transport is applied to the Iu interface and RTCP is supported, during a specified measurement period, the ratio is calculated according to the following formula: Ratio = duration of RTP delay jitter exceeding threshold/total active duration (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Loss Rate of RTP Packets Received over a Single IP Path: This measurement item provides the loss rate of RTP packets received over a single IP path during a specified measurement period. Updated: When IP transport is applied to the Iu interface and RTCP is supported, each time the Iu UP transmits an RTCP packet during a specified measurement period, the number of packets lost during the period increases by the number indicated in the RTCP packet. (Each RTCP packet needs to contain the number of packets lost during the period.) Then, based on the number of RTP packets received over the IP path, the RTP packet loss rate on the IP path can be calculated according to the following formula: Packet loss rate = number of packets lost/(number of packets lost + number of RTP packets received) (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Total Number of RTP Packets Received over a Single IP Path: This measurement item provides the total number of RTP packets received over a single IP path during a specified measurement period. This item is used to check the status of packet reception over a single IP path. Updated: When IP transport is applied to the Iu interface and RTCP is supported, this measurement item is increased by 1 each time the Iu UP receives a downlink RTP data packet during a specified measurement period. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Total Number of RTP Packets Transmitted over a Single IP Path: This measurement item provides the total number of RTP packets transmitted over a single IP path during a specified measurement period. This item is used to check the status of packet transmission over a single IP path. Updated: When IP transport is applied to the Iu interface and RTCP is supported, this measurement item is incremented by 1 each time the Iu UP transmits an uplink data packet or an in-band signaling packet during a specified measurement period. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Ratio of Duration of RTT Exceeding Threshold to Total Active Duration: This measurement item provides the ratio of the time during which the Round Trip Time (RTT) exceeds the threshold to the total time during which an IP path is active. This measurement is specific to the single IP path during a specified measurement period. Updated: When IP transport is applied to the Iu interface and RTCP is supported, during a specified measurement period, the ratio is calculated according to the following formula: Ratio = duration of RTT exceeding threshold/total active duration (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of CS Domain Inter-RAT Outgoing Handover Attempts: This measurement item provides the number of UEHANDOVER FROM UTRAN COMMAND messages sent by the SRNC to a UE. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point C as shown in Figure 1. When the SRNC sends the UE a HANDOVER FROM UTRAN COMMAND message during the CS domain inter-RAT outgoing handover, the SRNC measures this item. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of CS Domain Inter-RAT Incoming Handover Commitments: This measurement item provides the number of CS domain inter-RAT incoming handover commitments in the RNC. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point C, as shown in Figure 1. After the RNC sends the CN a RELOCATION REQUEST ACKNOWLEDGE message to complete the CS domain inter-RAT handover preparation, and if it receives a HANDOVER TO UTRAN COMPLETE message from the UE or a RADIO LINK RESTORE INDICATION message from the NodeB, the RNC measures only one of the messages. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Attempted CS Inter-RAT Outgoing Handovers Between NeighboringCells: This measurement item provides the number of HANDOVER FROM UTRAN COMMAND messages that the RNC sends to the UE. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point C, as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC sends a HANDOVER FROM UTRAN COMMAND message to the UE in the CS domain inter-RAT handover procedure, the RNC measures this item for each pair of source and target cells. Here, the best cell that the UE camps on before the inter-RAT handover is the source cell, and the cell that the UE wants to hand over to is the target cell. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Requests for UE-originated PS Domain Outgoing Inter-RAT Handovers(Cell): This measurement item provides the number of requests for UE-originated PS domain outgoing inter-RAT handovers. If the UE is in CELL_FACH, CELL_PCH, or URA_PCH state after setting up PS service in the WCDMA system, it can reselect a GPRS network according to cell reselection rules. After the reselection, the UE needs to re-establish the PS service. During this procedure, the 2.5G SGSN queries the context of PS RAB that is set up by the UE in the WCDMA system through an SRNS CONTEXT REQUEST procedure. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives an SRNS CONTEXT REQUEST message. In this case, the RNC measures the item in each cell that the UE camps on before the relocation. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Attempted PS Inter-RAT Outgoing Handovers Between NeighboringCells: This measurement item provides the number of attempted PS inter-RAT outgoing handovers between neighboring cells. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B, as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC sends the UE a CELL CHANGE ORDER FROM UTRAN message during the PS inter-RAT handover, it measures this item for each pair of source and target cells. Here, the best cell that the UE camps on before the inter-RAT handover is the source cell, and the cell that the UE wants to hand over to is the target cell. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of UE-Initiated PS Domain Inter-RAT Incoming Handover: This measurement item provides the number of PS domain inter-RAT incoming handover requests initiated by the UE. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A, as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC receives from the UE an RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message with the cause of Inter-RAT Cell change order, the RNC measures this item. Figure1 (6810)

RNC Counter: Number of UE-Initiated PS Domain Inter-RAT Outgoing Handover Requests: This measurement item provides the number of PS domain inter-RAT outgoing handover requests initiated by the UE. A UE in CELL_FACH, CELL_PCH or URA_PCH state using PS domain services may initiate a WCDMA-to-GPRS cell reselection procedure according to the cell reselection criteria. When the UE reselects a GPRS cell, it shall set up PS domain services again. In this case, the 2.5 G SGSN shall initiate an SRNS context transfer procedure by sending a SRNS CONTEXT REQUEST message to the RNC to request the RAB PDP context information of the UE established in the WCDMA network. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A, as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC receives a SRNS CONTEXT REQUEST message, it measures this item. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of PS Domain Inter-RAT Outgoing Handover Commitments Initiated by RNC: This measurement item provides the number of CELL CHANGE ORDER FROM UTRAN messages sent by the RNC. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B, as shown in Figure 1. When the SRNC sends a CELL CHANGE ORDER FROM UTRAN message to the UE during PS domain inter-RAT outgoing handover, the SRNC measures this item. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Timeouts of Waiting for IU RELEASE COMMAND Messages DuringOutgoing Inter-RAT PS Handovers Initiated by the RNC (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of timeouts of waiting for IU RELEASE COMMAND messages during outgoing inter-RAT PS handovers initiated by the RNC. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. During an outgoing inter-RAT PS handover, after the RNC sends a CELL CHANGE ORDER FROM UTRAN message, the RNC starts the associated timer and waits for the response from the UE. If the RNC receives no response from the UE and the waiting for an IU RELEASE COMMAND message from the CN is timed out, the RNC sends an IU RELEASE REQUEST message to the CN. Then, the RNC measures the item in the best cell that the UE camps on before the handover. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of Successful Cell Changes During PS Domain Inter-RAT OutgoingHandovers Initiated by RNC: This measurement item provides the number of successful cell changes during PS domain inter-RAT outgoing handovers initiated by the RNC. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point C, as shown in Figure 1. During PS domain inter-RAT outgoing handover, when the RNC sends a CELL CHANGE ORDER FROM UTRAN message, and if it receives an IU RELEASE COMMAND message with the cause of Successful Relocation, Normal Release or Network Optimization, it indicates that the CELL CHANGE procedure is successful. Number of UL or DL Congestions on Iub Interface: This measurement item provides the number of uplink or downlink congestions on the Iub Interface. Updated: The RNC measures this item on the NodeB basis when it finds that there are congestions on the Iub interface in the uplink or the downlink in a measurement period. Note: When the residual bandwidth on the Iub interface is smaller than the reserved congestion bandwidth threshold, it indicates that congestion occurs on the Iub interface. Once non-congestion is changed into congestion, the measurement is triggered. For the same congestion, the measurement is triggered only once. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Load Balancing: The measurement items provide the number of times that the UEs perform load balancing on the CS domain during CN node selection when the RNC processes the initial direct transfer message. VS.IU.LdBalRtCS.IMSI provides the number of times that the IMSI UEs perform load balancing during CN node selection. VS.IU.LdBalRtCS.InValidNRI provides the number of times that the TMSI UEs perform load balancing because of invalid NRI route, not including that caused by NULL-NRI or CN failure. VS.IU.LdBalRtCS.IMEI provides the number of times that the IMEI UEs perform load balancing during CN node selection. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A, as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC selects a certain CN node by load balancing, sends an INITIAL UE MESSAGE message to the CS domain, it measures this item according to IDNNS carried by UE. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Downlink Traffic of MBMS PS Domain of RNC for each Operator: This measurement item provides the downlink traffic of all the MBMS services in the PS domain of the RNC for each Operator. The item is measured only when the RAN sharing function is switched on. Updated: The RNC periodically takes the samples of the downlink traffic values (in kbit/s) of all the MBMS services in the PS domain for each Operator. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC calculates the mean sample (divide the accumulated value by the sampling times). The downlink traffic of all the MBMS services in the PS domain refers to the traffic measured at the RLC layer. The data does not include the RLC head data. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: DL Traffic of MBMS PS Domain in RNC: This measurement item provides the downlink traffic of all the MBMS services in the PS domain within the RNC. Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample from the downlink traffic values of all the MBMS services in the PS domain. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated traffic values by the number of samples to obtain the mean downlink traffic of all the MBMS services in the PS domain. The downlink traffic of all the MBMS services in the PS domain refers to the traffic measured at the RLC layer. The data does not include the RLC head data. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Maximum Downlink Traffic of MBMS PS Domain of RNC for each Operator: This measurement item provides the maximum downlink traffic of all the MBMS services in the PS domain of the RNC for each Operator. Updated: The RNC periodically takes the samples of the downlink traffic values (in kbit/s) of all the MBMS services in the PS domain for each Operator. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC calculates the maximum sample value. The downlink traffic of all the MBMS services in the PS domain refers to the traffic measured at the RLC layer. The data does not include the head data of RLC. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Maximum DL Traffic of MBMS PS Domain in RNC: This measurement item provides the maximum downlink traffic of all the MBMS services in the PS domain within the RNC. comment: Mean Number of UEs in PTP MBMS Service (Cell): This measurement item provides the mean number of UEs in PTP MBMS service in a cell. Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample from the number of UEs in PTP MBMS Service in a cell. Number of Setup Requests of PTM MBMS Service (cell): This measurement item provides the number of setup requests of PTM MBMS service in a cell. Updated: When the RNC initiates the setup of PTM MBMS service ,the RNC measures the item, as shown in Figure 1. . Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful Setups of PTM MBMS Service (cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful setups of PTM MBMS RB in a cell. Updated: When the RB of PTM MBMS service is successful set up ,the RNC measures the item. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Requests for PTP MBMS Setup (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of requests for setup of Point-to-Point (PTP) MBMS services in a cell. Updated: After the UE initiates an MBMS setup request, the RNC measures the item when the RNC initiates PTP RB setup based on the request of the UE. If the UE applies for more than one service, the RNC measures the item once for each service. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Abnormal Releases of PTP MBMS Services for Different Causes (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of abnormal releases of PTP MBMS services for different causes in a cell. Updated: If an unexpected event occurs, for example, for the RF reason on the air interface, the associated PTP RB is released. At that time, the RNC measures the item. If more than one RB (one RB for one service) is released at the same time, the RNC measures the item once for release of each RB. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Normal Releases of PTP MBMS Services (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of normal releases of PTP MBMS services in a cell. Updated: After a PTP RB is set up, the RNC measures this item in the following conditions: the UE initiates the RB release, the RNC initiates the RB release for transition from PTP to PTM, the RB release is performed because the SGSN initiates MBMS SESSION STOP, and the RNC initiates the RB release because of relocation. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful PTP MBMS Setups (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful setups of Point-to-Point (PTP) MBMS services in a cell. Updated: After the UE initiates an MBMS setup request, the RNC initiates PTP RB setup based on the request of the UE. When the PTP RB is successfully set up, the RNC measures the item. Unavailability Ratio: This measurement item provides the unavailability ratio of a single NodeB, that is, the out-of-service ratio of a single NodeB. Updated: This item is measured through the following formula: VS.NodeB.Ratio.of.UnavailTime.OM = VS.NodeB.UnavailTime.OM/measurement period. (6810)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN SUM(vs_nodeb_unavailtime_om) ELSE AVG(vs_nodeb_unavailtime_om) END
comment: NodeB Unavailability Time: This measurement item provides the unavailability time of a NodeB, that is, the out-of-service time of a NodeB. The NodeB is unavailable in the following conditions: (1) The NodeB fails, (2) All the cells are deactivated, (3) The RNC fails. Note: In the measurement period, the RNC does not add the duration of carrier shutdown to the cell unavailability time. Updated: The RNC measures this item based on the accumulated unavailability time of the NodeB in a measurement period. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of Normally Released RABs in DRNC Cell: Number of CS AMR service RABs normally released in the best cell that belongs to the DRNC Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A, as shown in Figure 1, after the RNC receives an IU RELEASE COMMAND message, it releases relevant RABs and sends an IU RELEASE COMPLETE message to the CN. If the IU RELEASE COMMAND message is initiated by the CN, or before that the RNC sends an IU RELEASE REQUEST message to the CN with the cause of User Inactivity or the UE initiates a signaling connection release, the RNC measures each item according to different types of domains on Iur Interface. . Figure1 The measurement is triggered at point B, as shown in Figure 2, when the RNC receives the RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message where there are RABs to be released, the RNC releases related RABs and sends the RAB ASSIGNMENT RESPONSE message to the CN. If the RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message is initiated by the CN, or if the RNC sends RAB RELEASE REQUEST message to the CN due to User Inactivity before the CN initiates the RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message, or if the UE initiates a signaling connection release, the RNC measures each item according to different domains on Iur Interface. . Figure2 Number of normally released RABs in DRNC cell on Iur interface  (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Compression Ratio of DL Packet Headers Under ROHC: This measurement item provides the ratio of the packet header size after all downlink PS packets undergo Robust Header Compression (ROHC) to the header size before the ROHC during a measurement period in the RNC. This measurement item is valid when the ROHC algorithm is configured. Updated: When a PDCP entity receives a downlink packet, it judges whether the packet is configured with ROHC. If the packet is not configured with ROHC, the PDCP entity does not report this measurement item. If the packet is configured with ROHC, the PDCP entity goes through the sub-headers of the packet to obtain the chain size before adding the size to the item DL Packet Header Size before Compression. After the compression, the PDCP entity then adds the new sub-header chain size to the item DL Packet Header Size after Compression. At the end of the measurement period, the PDCP entity reports the two item values to the performance measurement unit and resets the two items. Then the performance measurement unit calculates the compression ratio of the downlink packet headers under ROHC based on the reported values of DL Packet Header Size before Compression and DL Packet Header Size after Compression. The equation is as shown in Figure 1: Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Compression Ratio of DL Packets Under ROHC: This measurement item provides the ratio of the packet size after all downlink PS packets undergo Robust Header Compression (ROHC) to the packet size before the ROHC during a measurement period in the RNC. This measurement item is valid when the ROHC algorithm is configured. Updated: When a PDCP entity receives a downlink packet, it judges whether the packet is configured with ROHC. If the packet is not configured with ROHC, the PDCP entity does not report this measurement item. If the packet is configured with ROHC, the number of compressed downlink packets increases by 1. Meanwhile, the PDCP entity adds the initial packet size to the item DL Packet Size before Compression. After the compression, it adds the packet size to the item DL Packet Size after Compression. At the end of the measurement period, the PDCP entity reports the two item values to the performance measurement unit and resets the two items. Then the performance measurement unit calculates the compression ratio of the downlink packets under ROHC based on the reported values of DL Packet Size before Compression and DL Packet Size after Compression. The equation is as shown in Figure 1: Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Ratio of UL ROHC Decompression Failures to Total UL ROHC DecompressionOperations: This measurement item provides the ratio of the number of UL PS packets failing to be decompressed by Robust Header Compression (ROHC) to the total number of UL packets undergoing ROHC decompression during a measurement period in the RNC. This measurement item is valid when the ROHC algorithm is configured. Updated: When a PDCP entity receives an uplink packet, it judges whether the packet is configured with ROHC. If the packet is configured with ROHC, the value of the item Number of Uplink Packets to Be Decompressed increases by 1. Then, if the decompression fails, the value of the item Number of UL Packets Failing to Be Decompressed increases by 1. At the end of the measurement period, the PDCP entity reports the two item values to the performance measurement unit and resets the two items. Then, the performance measurement unit calculates the ratio of Number of Uplink Packets Failing to Be Decompressed to Number of UL Packets to Be Decompressed. The equation is as shown in Figure 1: Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Downlink Traffic of R99 PS Domain of RNC for each Operator: This measurement item provides the downlink traffic of all the R99 services in the PS domain of the RNC for each Operator. The item is measured only when the RAN sharing function is switched on. Updated: The RNC periodically takes the samples of the downlink traffic values (in kbit/s) of all the R99 services in the PS domain for each Operator. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC calculates the mean sample (divide the accumulated value by the sampling times). The downlink traffic of all the R99 services in the PS domain refers to the traffic measured at the RLC layer. The data does not include the RLC head data. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: DL Traffic of R99 PS Domain in RNC: This measurement item provides the downlink traffic of all the R99 services in the PS domain within the RNC. Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample from the downlink traffic values of all the R99 services in the PS domain. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated traffic values by the number of samples to obtain the mean downlink traffic of all the R99 services in the PS domain. The downlink traffic of all the R99 services in the PS domain refers to the traffic measured at the RLC layer. The data does not include the RLC head data. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

At the end of the measurement period, the RNC calculates the maximum sample value. The downlink traffic of all the R99 services in the PS domain refers to the traffic measured at the RLC layer. The data does not include the head data of RLC. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

At the end of the measurement period, the RNC calculates the maximum downlink traffic of all the R99 services in PS domain within the RNC. RNC Counter: Maximum Uplink Traffic of R99 PS Domain of RNC for each Operator: This measurement item provides the maximum uplink traffic of all the R99 services in the PS domain of the RNC for each Operator. The item is measured only when the RAN sharing function is switched on. Updated: The RNC periodically takes the samples of the uplink traffic values (in kbit/s) of all the R99 services in the PS domain for each Operator. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC calculates the maximum sample value. The uplink traffic of all the R99 services in the PS domain refers to the traffic measured at the RLC layer. The data does not include the head data of RLC. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Maximum UL Traffic of R99 PS Domain in RNC: This measurement item provides the maximum uplink traffic of all the R99 services in the PS domain within the RNC. Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample from the uplink traffic values of all the R99 services in the PS domain. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC calculates the maximum uplink traffic of all the R99 services in the PS domain within the RNC. The uplink traffic of all the R99 services in the PS domain refers to the traffic obtained at the RLC layer. The data does not include the RLC head data. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Uplink Traffic of R99 PS Domain of RNC for each Operator: This measurement item provides the uplink traffic of all the R99 services in the PS domain of the RNC for each Operator. The item is measured only when the RAN sharing function is switched on. Updated: The RNC periodically takes the samples of the uplink traffic values (in kbit/s) of all the R99 services in the PS domain for each Operator. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC calculates the mean sample (divide the accumulated value by the sampling times). The uplink traffic of all the R99 services in the PS domain refers to the traffic measured at the RLC layer. The data does not include the RLC head data. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: UL Traffic of R99 PS Domain in RNC: This measurement item provides the uplink traffic of all the R99 services in the PS domain within the RNC. Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample from the uplink traffic values of all the R99 services in the PS domain. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated values by the number of samples to obtain the mean uplink traffic of all the R99 services in the PS domain. The uplink traffic of all the R99 services in the PS domain refers to the traffic obtained at the RLC layer. The data does not include the RLC head data. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

comment: RNC Counter: Mean Number of UEs Setting Up Different IMS Services: Mean Number of UEs of Different IMS Services (PTT over Cellular) Updated: The RNC periodically takes samples from the number of UEs that set up different IMS services. Maximum Delay of RAB Setup on DCH in the CS Domain (Cell): This measurement item provides the maximum delay of RAB setup on DCH in the CS domain. The measurement is undertaken in the best cell that is under the SRNC. Updated: When the best cell in the active set is under the SRNC, the RNC measures the item in the best cell. As shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives an RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message at point A, it records the time T1 if it judges that the message indicates RAB setup on the DCH in the CS domain. Then, when the RNC receives a RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE message and sends an RAB ASSIGNMENT RESPONSE message to the CN at point B, the RNC records the time T2. Take the difference between T1 and T2 as T. Then, T is the signaling delay of the RAB assignment and setup procedure. This measurement item takes the maximum value of T in the cell in a measurement period. Figure1 (6810)

The measurement is undertaken in the best cell that is under the SRNC. Updated: When the best cell in the active set is under the SRNC, the RNC measures the item in the best cell. As shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives an RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message at point A, it records the time T1 if it judges that the message indicates RAB setup on the DCH in the PS domain. Then, when the RNC receives a RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE message and sends an RAB ASSIGNMENT RESPONSE message to the CN at point B, the RNC records the time T2. Take the difference between T1 and T2 as T. Then, T is the signaling delay of the RAB assignment and setup procedure. This measurement item takes the mean value of T in the cell in a measurement period. Figure1 (6810)

RNC Counter: Number of Released PS RABs Triggered by RNC at Different Max DL Bit Rates: Number of released PS RABs triggered by RNC (max DL bit rate = 384 kbit/s) Updated: All the previous items take statistics in the following three cases: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. After the PS RABs have been set up, the RNC sends a RAB RELEASE REQUEST message to the CN due to an exception, for example, GTPU abnormity. When the RNC receives a RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message from the CN and the cause value is not Normal Release, after it responses with a RAB ASSIGNMENT RESPONSE message, the RNC measures these items according to different maximum downlink bit rates. Figure1 The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 2. When the CS RABs have been successfully set up, the RNC sends an RAB RELEASE REQUEST message to the CN due to an exception, for example, GTPU abnormity. Then, the CN sends an IU RELEASE COMMAND message to the RNC. When the RNC receives this message and the cause value is not Normal Release, it releases the related resources and sends an IU RELEASE COMPLETE message to the CN. At this time, the measurement is triggered and the RNC measures these items according to different maximum downlink bit rates. Figure2 The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 3. When the CS RABs have been successfully set up, the RNC sends an IU RELEASE REQUEST message to the CN due to an exception. Then, the CN sends an IU RELEASE COMMAND message to the RNC. When the RNC receives this message, it releases the related resources and sends an IU RELEASE COMPLETE message to the CN. At this time, the measurement is triggered and the RNC measures these items according to different maximum downlink bit rates.The reasons for the release of RAB can be Repeated Integrity Checking Failure (37), Radio Connection With UE Lost (46), OM Intervention (113), Unspecified Failure (115), and so on. For details, refer to 3GPP TS 25.413. Figure3 (6810)

RNC Counter: Mean Number of CS RABs: This measurement item provides the mean number of CS RABs in the RNC within a measurement period. Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample from the number of CS RABs. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the total number of CS RABs by the number of samples to obtain the mean number of CS RABs. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Mean Number of PS RABs: This measurement item provides the mean number of PS RABs in the RNC within a measurement period. Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample from the number of PS RABs. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the total number of PS RABs by the number of samples to obtain the mean number of PS RABs. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Mean Queuing Duration of PS RABs (Cell): Mean queuing duration of PS RABs for conversational services in the best cell Updated: After the RNC receives a RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message from the CN, the RAB enters a waiting queue. When the resource are available, the RAB exits the queue. The queuing duration is from enter time to exit time. If the PS RABs are established, the RNC measures the items in the best cell that the UE camps on. (6810)

Mean Queuing Duration of PS RABs (Cell): Mean queuing duration of PS RABs for streaming services in the best cell Updated: After the RNC receives a RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message from the CN, the RAB enters a waiting queue. Updated: The measurement is triggered at points A and B, as shown in Figure 1: Figure1 At point A, the RNC records the time (T1) when receiving a RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message for establishing PS RABs on the DCH. Mean And Maximum Number of Occupied Codes (Cell): The measurement items provide the mean number and the maximum number of occupied codes in a cell. The occupied codes are the codes occupied by the common channel, R99 user, and HS-DSCH. The code number is normalized to SF = 256, that is, converted to the code number when SF = 256. The way of the normalization to SF = 256 is to multiply the number when SF = k by 256/k. Updated: The RNC takes a sample from the number of occupied codes in a cell every five seconds and normalize the number to SF = 256. Then calculate the sum of the normalized numbers. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated number by the number of samples to obtain the mean number of occupied codes in the cell within the measurement period. The maximum number of occupied codes that is reported to the RNC is defined as the maximum number of occupied codes in the cell within the measurement period.. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)
