edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN AVG(vs_rac_dl_totaltrffactor) ELSE SUM(vs_rac_dl_totaltrffactor) END
comment: Mean Number of DL Equivalent Voice UEs in CEL_DCH State (Cell): This measurement item provides the mean number of DL equivalent voice UEs in CELL_DCH state in a cell. Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample of DL equivalent voice UEs in CELL_DCH state. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated number of DL equivalent voice UEs in CELL_DCH state by the number of samples to obtain the mean number. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Mean Number of DL Equivalent Voice UEs in CEL_DCH State (Cell): This measurement item provides the mean number of DL equivalent voice UEs in CELL_DCH state in a cell. Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample of DL equivalent voice UEs in CELL_DCH state. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated number of DL equivalent voice UEs in CELL_DCH state by the number of samples to obtain the mean number. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful Cell Resource Requests for UE Hard Handover (Cell): After the RNC receives an measurement report from a UE, it shall request cell resource for successful hard handover to a new cell. This measurement item provides the number of successful cell resource requests for hard handover. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC requests cell resource for hard handover after receiving a measurement report from a UE. If the request succeeds, the RNC measures this item in the cell that the UE camps on. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Cell Resource Requests for UE Hard Handover (Cell): After the RNC receives an measurement report from a UE, it shall request cell resource for hard handover to a new cell. This measurement item provides the number of cell resource requests for hard handover. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC requests cell resource for hard handover after receiving a measurement report from a UE. In this case, the RNC measures the item in the cell that the UE camps on. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Failed Incoming Hard Handovers due to Insufficient DL CodeResources (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of failed incoming hard handovers due to insufficient DL code resources. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC requests cell resource for hard handover after receiving an inter-frequency measurement report from a UE, and if the DL code assignment fails, the RNC measures this item in the target cell to which the UE is handed over. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful Cell Resource Requests for New Call Setup (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful cell resource requests for the setup of a new call. Updated: As shown in Figure 1, after receiving an RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message from the CN, the RNC requests cell resources for the UE. After the request is successful, as shown at point B in the figure, the RNC measures the item in the cell that the UE camps on. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Cell Resource Requests for New Call Setup (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of cell resource requests for new call setup. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives a RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message from the CN. In this case, the RNC measures this item in the cell that the UE camps on. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful Cell Resource Requests due to UE ServiceReconfiguration (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful cell resource requests due to UE service reconfiguration. Updated: When the RNC receives a RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message with the cause of RABs To Be Modified, it shall request cell resource again for this UE. If the request succeeds, the RNC measures this item in the cell that the UE camps on. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Cell Resource Requests due to UE Service Reconfiguration (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of cell resource requests due to UE service reconfiguration. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. When receiving a RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message with the cause value of RABs To Be Modified, the RNC requests cell resources again for this UE. In this case, the RNC measures this item in the cell that the UE camps on. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful Cell Resource Requests for UE Soft Handover (Cell): After the RNC receives an intra-frequency measurement report from a UE, it shall request cell resource for successful soft handover to a new cell. This measurement item provides the number of successful cell resource requests for soft handover. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC requests cell resource for soft handover upon reception of an intra-frequency measurement report from a UE. If the request succeeds, the RNC measures this item in the cell that the UE camps on. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Cell Resource Requests for UE Soft Handover (Cell): After the RNC receives an intra-frequency measurement report from a UE, it shall request cell resource for soft handover to a new cell. This measurement item provides the number of cell resource requests for soft handover. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC requests cell resource for soft handover after receiving an intra-frequency measurement report from a UE. In this case, the RNC measures this item in the cell that the UE camps on. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Failed Services due to Congestion (Cell): Number of failures in each cell to request UL CE resources in the SHO procedure Updated: The measurement is triggered when RNC reject UE to access because of congestion. ( Note: The CAC (Call Admission Control) is divided two parts. The first part is pre-estimating whether the resource is enough or not and decides the target accessing Qos. The second part is assigning the resource to the access request. To avoid the meaningless increasing of items in DCCC pre-estimating procedure, the measurement points of following measurement items are set at the point when the access requests are rejected in the second part: - VS.RAC.DCCC.Fail.ULCE.Cong - VS.RAC.DCCC.Fail.DLCE.Cong - VS.RAC.DCCC.Fail.ULLD.Cong - VS.RAC.DCCC.Fail.DLLD.Cong - VS.RAC.DCCC.Fail.OVSF.Cong (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful Cell Resource Requests due to UE RRC State Transition(Cell): When a UE transits from CELL_FACH to CELL_DCH state or from CELL_DCH to CELL_FACH state, the RNC shall request cell resource for this UE. This measurement item provides the number of successful cell resource requests due to UE RRC state transition. Updated: The measurement is triggered when the RNC successfully requests cell resource for a UE due to UE state transition between CELL_FACH and CELL-DCH. In this case, the RNC measures this item in the cell that the UE camps on. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

comment: Mean Number of UL Equivalent Voice UEs in CEL_DCH State (Cell): This measurement item provides the mean number of UL equivalent voice UEs in CELL_DCH state in a cell. Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample from the number of UL equivalent voice UEs in CELL_DCH state. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated number of UL equivalent voice UEs in CELL_DCH state by the number of samples to obtain the mean number. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of CS-Oriented PAGING Messages from the CN: This measurement item provides the number of CS-oriented PAGING messages from the CN to the RNC. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC receives a PAGING message from the CN, the measurement of this item is triggered if the CN Domain Indicator IE in the message indicates the CS domain. The consecutive retransmissions of the same PAGING message by RNC are not repeatedly counted. But the message repeatedly receives from CN are repearedly counted. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of Failures to Respond to CS-Oriented PAGING Messages from the CN: This measurement item provides the number of failures to respond to CS-oriented PAGING messages from the CN to the RNC. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC receives from the CN a PAGING message in which the CN Domain Indicator IE indicates the CS domain, the measurement of this item is triggered if the RNC does not send a Paging type 1 or Paging type 2 message. The reason why the RNC does not send a Paging type 1 or Paging type 2 message might be Iu flow control, high CPU usage, or PCH congestion. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of Paging Messages to UEs in Idle Mode: This measurement item provides the number of PAGING TYPE 1 messages from the RNC to the UEs in idle mode after it receives the PAGING messages from the CN. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC receives a PAGING message from the CN, and if the paged UE is in idle mode, the RNC sends a PAGING TYPE 1 message to the cell in the paged area. In this case, the RNC measures this item. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of Successful Paging Messages to UEs in Idle Mode: This measurement item provides the number of RRC CONNECTION REQUEST messages from the UEs to the RNC that has sent a PAGING TYPE 1 messages to page the UEs in idle mode. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point C as shown in Figure 1. The RNC measures this item when it receives an RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message from a UE with one of the following causes: Terminating Conversational Call,Terminating Streaming Call,Terminating Interactive Call,Terminating Background Call,Terminating High Priority Signaling,Terminating Low Priority Signaling,Terminating cause unknown. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of PS-Oriented PAGING Messages from the CN: This measurement item provides the number of PS-oriented PAGING messages from the CN to the RNC. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC receives a PAGING message from the CN, the measurement of this item is triggered if the CN Domain Indicator IE in the message indicates the PS domain. The consecutive retransmissions of the same PAGING message are not repeatedly counted. But the message repeatedly receives from CN are repearedly counted. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of Failures to Respond to PS-Oriented PAGING Messages from the CN: This measurement item provides the number of failures to respond to PS-oriented PAGING messages from the CN to the RNC. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC receives from the CN a PAGING message in which the CN Domain Indicator IE indicates the PS domain, the measurement of this item is triggered if the RNC does not send a Paging type 1 or Paging type 2 message. The reason why the RNC does not send a Paging type 1 or Paging type 2 message might be Iu flow control, high CPU usage, or PCH congestion. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of DL Signaling PDUs Discarded by RLC-AM (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of signaling PDUs discarded in the downlink by the RLC in acknowledged mode during the transmission. Number of Traffic PDUs Retransmitted by RLC-AM (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of traffic PDUs retransmitted by the RLC in acknowledged mode. Updated: The RNC measures this item when the downlink traffic PDUs are retransmitted by the RLC in acknowledged mode on the user plane. (6810)

Number of Traffic PDUs Delivered by RLC-AM (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of traffic PDUs delivered by the RLC in acknowledged mode. It doesn't include the PUDs retransmitted. Updated: The RNC measures this item when the downlink traffic PDUs are delivered by the RLC in acknowledged mode on the user plane. (6810)

Number of RLs Provided by Other Cells in RNC (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of RLs provided by other cells in the RNC for UEs in a cell. Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample from the number of RLs provided by other cells for UEs of a cell. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated number by the number of samples to obtain the number of RLs provided by other cells for UEs in this cell. (6810)

Number of RRC Connection Requests on CCH (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of times that the RNC decides to set up the RRC connection on the CCH after receiving an RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message from a UE in a cell. Updated: When the RNC receives an RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message from a UE The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, and decides to set up the RRC connection on the CCH. In this case, the RNC measures the item based on the cell that the UE camps on. If the received RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message is repeatedly reported by the UE, the measurement will not be triggered. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of RRC Connection Requests on DCH (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of times that the RNC decides to set up the RRC connection on the DCH after receiving an RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message from a UE in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives the RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message from a UE and decides to set up the RRC connection on the DCH. In this case, the RNC measures the item based on the cell that the UE camps on. If the received RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message is repeatedly reported by the UE, the measurement will not be triggered. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of Processed RRC Connection Requests (CCH): This measurement item provides the number of RRC CONNECTION REQUEST messages that the RNC receives from the UEs and through which the RNC judges that the RRC connections need to be set up on the CCH. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC receives an RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message it allocates associated resources according to the request causes. If the RNC judges based on the resource allocation that the RRC connection needs to be set up on the CCH, the measurement of this item is triggered. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of RRC Connection Requests (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of RRC CONNECTION REQUEST messages processed by the RNC in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives a RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message from the UE, if the message is processed by the RNC (the RNC requests resources and try to set up the RRC connection) and is not repeatedly reported by the same UE (in other words, the measurement is performed only once for repeated RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message sent by the same UE from different cells in the same sub-system), the RNC measures the item on the cell that the UEs camp on. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of Processed RRC Connection Requests (DCH): This measurement item provides the number of RRC CONNECTION REQUEST messages that the RNC receives from the UEs and through which the RNC judges that the RRC connections need to be set up on the DCH. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC receives an RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message, it allocates associated resources according to the request causes. If the RNC judges based on the resource allocation that the RRC connection needs to be set up on the DCH, the measurement of this item is triggered. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of Processed RRC Connection Requests: This measurement item provides the number of RRC CONNECTION REQUEST messages actually processed by the RNC. This item includes VS.RRC.AttConnEstab.CCH and VS.RRC.AttConnEstab.DCH. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. The UE may send multiple RRC CONNECTION REQUEST messages from different cells to increase the probability of successfully setting up the RRC connection. For these repeated requests, the RNC measures this item only once. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Signaling Delay of RRC Connection Setup on CCH (Cell): Maximum signaling delay of RRC connection setup on the CCH in a cell Updated: The measurement is triggered at points A and C as shown in Figure 1. Figure1 At point A, the RNC records the time (T1) when receiving an RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message from a UE. At point C, the RNC records the time (T2) when receiving the RRC CONNECTION SETUP COMPLETE message from the UE. Suppose T represents the signaling delay of this RRC connection setup on the CCH. Then, T=T2-T1. Through T of each RRC connection setup on the CCH in a measurement period, you can obtain the previous mentioned item values. (6810)

Signaling Delay of RRC Connection Setup on CCH (Cell): Mean signaling delay of RRC connection setup on the CCH in a cell Updated: The measurement is triggered at points A and C as shown in Figure 1. Figure1 At point A, the RNC records the time (T1) when receiving an RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message from a UE. At point C, the RNC records the time (T2) when receiving the RRC CONNECTION SETUP COMPLETE message from the UE. Suppose T represents the signaling delay of this RRC connection setup on the CCH. Then, T=T2-T1. Through T of each RRC connection setup on the CCH in a measurement period, you can obtain the previous mentioned item values. (6810)

Signaling Delay of RRC Connection Setup on DCH (Cell): Maximum signaling delay of RRC connection setup on the DCH in a cell Updated: The measurement is triggered at points A and C as shown in Figure 1. Figure1 At point A, the RNC records the time (T1) when receiving the RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message from a UE. At point C, the RNC records the time (T2) when receiving the RRC CONNECTION SETUP COMPLETE message from the UE. Suppose T represents the signaling delay of this RRC connection setup on DCH. Then, T=T2-T1. Through T of each RRC connection setup on the DCH in a measurement period, you can obtain the previous mentioned item values. VS.RRC.ConnEstabTimeMax.DCH indicates the maximum value of T in the cell in the measurement period, VS.RRC.ConnEstabTimeMean.DCH indicates the mean value of T in the cell in the measurement period. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Signaling Delay of RRC Connection Setup on DCH (Cell): Mean signaling delay of RRC connection setup on the DCH in a cell Updated: The measurement is triggered at points A and C as shown in Figure 1. Figure1 At point A, the RNC records the time (T1) when receiving the RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message from a UE. At point C, the RNC records the time (T2) when receiving the RRC CONNECTION SETUP COMPLETE message from the UE. Suppose T represents the signaling delay of this RRC connection setup on DCH. Then, T=T2-T1. Through T of each RRC connection setup on the DCH in a measurement period, you can obtain the previous mentioned item values. VS.RRC.ConnEstabTimeMax.DCH indicates the maximum value of T in the cell in the measurement period, VS.RRC.ConnEstabTimeMean.DCH indicates the mean value of T in the cell in the measurement period. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of RRC Connection Releases due to Cell Update Failure with the Causeof Radio Link Failure (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of RRC connection releases due to cell update failure with the cause of radio link failure. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends an RRC CONNECTION RELEASE message to a UE due to cell update failure with the cause of radio link failure. In this case, the RNC measures the item in the cell that the UE selects to update.  In UTRAN 6900, the KPI counters of RAB setup and release is counted based on the best cell, but in the early release 6810 the counters of RRC release is counted based on per cell in the active set, in the current KPI analysis system, the statistical method is not logical, so change the counter based on the best cell. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

UTRAN 6810 : Number of RRC CONNECTION REQUEST Messages from the RNC During Incoming DRD(Cell): This measurement item provides the number of RRC CONNECTION REQUEST messages, sent by the RNC for incoming Direct Retry Decision (DRD), in the target cell that is under the SRNC. Updated: If the target cell for incoming RRC DRD is under the SRNC, when the RNC receives an RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message and the message is not a repeated report of a UE, the RNC measures the item on the target cell. If cell reselection happens during the incoming DRD, the measurement object is the last target cell. If RRC DRD procedure fails, the item will be measured in the original cell. UTRAN 6900 :Number of RRC Connection Setup Attempts with DRD in for Cell.In the previous release, the measurement point of the counter included two scenes as following: when RRC DRD succeeds, the counter will count in the target cell, when RRC DRC fails, the counter will count in the original camp cell.The measurement point is not logical that the meanings of the counter is not clear.So change the measurement point as following: the counter will count only when RRC DRD incoming is successful in the target cell. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of RRC Connection Reject Messages due to Iub Interface Failure (Cell): Number of RRC CONNECTION REJECT messages from the RNC to UEs in a cell due to AAL2 setup failure Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends an RRC CONNECTION REJECT message to a UE. In this case, the RNC measures the items according to different reject causes based on the cell that the UE camps on. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Initiated RRC Connection Setups (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of RRC CONNECTION SETUP messages sent by the RNC to UEs in a cell after the RNC receives the RRC CONNECTION REQUEST messages from the UEs. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends the RRC CONNECTION SETUP message to a UE. Before this, there are the following steps,The RNC receives an RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message from a UE.The RNC initiates an RRC connection setup procedure.The network side performs related operations successfully. The RNC measures the item based on the IDs of the cells that the UEs camp on. After receiving a repeated RRC CONNECTINO REQUEST message from the UE, the RNC will send again the RRC CONNECTION SETUP message to the UE. However, in such a case, the measurement will not be triggered. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of RRC Connection Setups: These two measurement items provide the number of RRC CONNECTION SETUP messages that the RNC sends to the UEs according to different channels for RRC connection setups. VS.RRC.SetupConnEstab: number of RRC CONNECTION SETUP messages that the RNC sends to the UEs. VS.RRC.SetupConnEstab.DCH: number of RRC CONNECTION SETUP messages that the RNC sends to the UEs and through which the RRC connections need to be set up on the DCHs. If the RNC receives a repeated RRC CONNECTINO REQUEST message from a UE, it will send the corresponding RRC CONNECTION SETUP message repeatedly to the UE but measures this item only once. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1. After the RNC receives an RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message from a UE, it initiates the RRC connection setup procedure and then sends an RRC CONNECTION SETUP message to the UE. When related operations on the network side are succeeded, the RNC measures these items. Figure1 (6810)

Number of NNI SAAL Link Alignment Failures: This measurement item provides the number of NNI SAAL link alignment failures. The RNC measures NNI SAAL links only. Updated: The measurement is triggered when the alignment of the NNI SAAL link fails during the link re-establishment. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of NNI SAAL Link Failures: This measurement item provides the number of NNI SAAL link failures. The failures may be caused by broken NNI SAAL link for any reason or alignment failure in the link setup procedure. The RNC measures NNI SAAL links only. Updated: The measurement is triggered when the NNI SAAL link transits from In Service state to Out of Service state or when the NNI SAAL link alignment fails. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of SAAL Link Failures due to Too High Bit Error Rate: This measurement item provides the number of SAAL link failures because the bit error rate is excessively high. The RNC measures NNI SAAL links only. Updated: The measurement is triggered when the SAAL layer management module releases an NNI SAAL link because too many packets on this link are lost. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of NNI SAAL Link Failures due to No Credit: This measurement item provides the number of NNI SAAL link failures due to no credit for a long time. The RNC measures NNI SAAL links only. NNI SAAL controls flow through sliding window. The credit refers to the size of the sliding window, which indicates namely the data transmit capacity of the local end. If the peer end fails to refresh the sliding window in time, the local end has no credit and cannot transmit data. At that time, the SAAL link starts the Timer-No_Credit. When getting back the credit, the SAAL link stops the timer. Updated: This measurement is triggered when the Timer-No_Credit expires. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of SAAL Link Failures due to NO_RESPONSE Timer Expiry: This measurement item provides the number of SAAL link failures due to no response from the peer end. Updated: The measurement is triggered as shown in Figure 1. The RNC sends a POLL message to the CN and starts Timer-No_Response to wait for the STAT report from the CN. If the RNC does not receive the report until the timer expires, this item shall be measured. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of PDUs Received by NNI SAAL Link with Error Code from Q to T: This measurement item provides the number of PDUs received by an SAAL link with the error code from Q to T. Error code Q: indicates the erroneous sequence number N(S) of an SD or POLL message. Error code R: indicates the erroneous sequence number N(PS) of a STAT message. Error code S: indicates an N(R) or LIST error of an STAT message. Error code T: indicates an N(R) or LIST error of an USTAT message. For details, see TABLE A.1/Q.2110. The RNC measures NNI SAAL links only. Updated: This measurement is triggered when the SAAL link receives a PDU with the error code of Q, R, S, or T. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Unsolicited or Inappropriate PDUs Received by NNI SAAL Link: This measurement item provides the number of unsolicited or inappropriate protocol data units (PDUs) received by SAAL NNI link. An unexpected PDU refers to the erroneous PDU received by the SAAL link with the error code from A to M. For details, see TABLE A.1/Q.2110. The RNC measures NNI SAAL links only. Updated: This measurement is triggered when the SAAL link receives an unexpected PDU, for example, when an idle SAAL link receives an SD PDU. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Retransmission Failures of NNI SAAL Link Connection ControlMessage.: This measurement item provides the number of failures in retransmitting an NNI SAAL link connection control message. The NNI SAAL link connection control messages include BGN, END, RS, and ER. For example, the SAAL link fails to receive a response from the peer end after resending a BGN message several times during the SAAL link establishment. The RNC measures NNI SAAL links only. Updated: The RNC sends a link connection control message (BGN, END, RS, or ER) on an SAAL link and starts timer TIMER_CC to wait for a response from the peer end. If the RNC does not receive the response from the peer end until the timer expires, it resends the link connection control message. This measurement is triggered when the RNC does not receive a response from the peer end according to the specified number of message retransmissions. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Retransmissions on SAAL Link due to Loss of Packet: This measurement item provides the number of retransmissions of a packet on the SAAL link due to loss of the packet. To provide reliable signaling transmission for the upper layer, the SAAL link retransmits the lost packet. Updated: This measurement is triggered when the SAAL link receives a USTAT or STAT message indicating the request for packet retransmission. BSC6900: Devide VS.SAAL.LnkErr.SDLossn into VS.SAAL.LnkErr.SDRetransRx and VS.SAAL.LnkErr.SDRetransTx to provide the number of retransmissions of the uplink and downlink lost packet on the SAAL link separately. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Cells Discarded by SAAL PVC due to Error Contents: This measurement item provides the number of cells discarded by the SAAL PVC due to error contents in the specified measurement period. The item indicates the status of the errors in the transmission cells on a single SAAL PVC. Updated: Samples are taken every five seconds in the specified measurement period. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Cells Discarded by SAAL PVC due to Error Packet Length: This measurement item provides the number of cells discarded by the SAAL PVC due to error packet length in the specified measurement period. The item indicates the status of the errors in the transmission cells on a single SAAL PVC. Updated: Samples are taken every five seconds in the specified measurement period. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

comment: In-Service Duration of NNI SAAL Link: This measurement item provides the in-service duration of an NNI SAAL link. The RNC measures NNI SAAL links only. When the RNC sends an ACTIVE SET UPDATE message to the UE during the soft handover procedure, the RNC measures this item for each pair of source and target cells. Here, the source cells refer to the cells that the UE camps on before the soft handover except the cell whose RL is released in this soft handover. Here, source cells refer to the cell that the UE camps on before the soft handover except the cells whose RLs are deleted in the soft handover. edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN AVG(vs_sho_as_1) ELSE SUM(vs_sho_as_1) END
comment: RNC Counter: Mean Number of UEs with One Radio Link: This measurement item provides the mean number of UEs with one Radio Link (RL) in the RNC. Updated: The RNC periodically takes a sample from the number of UEs with only one RL. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated number by the number of samples to obtain the mean number of UEs with only one RL in the measurement period. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN AVG(vs_sho_as_1rl) ELSE SUM(vs_sho_as_1rl) END
comment: Mean Number of UEs with One RL (Cell): This measurement item provides the mean number of UEs with only one RL in a cell. The cell belongs to active set. Updated: The RNC periodically samples the number of UEs with only one RL in a cell and the cell belongs to active set. At the end of every statistical cycle calculates the mean value by dividing the sum of sampled data by sampling times of current cycle. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Attempts to Perform Soft Handovers with Signaling Only asInitiated by the RNC (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of attempts in a cell to perform soft handovers when only signaling exists. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1. During a soft handover performed when only signaling exists, when the RNC sends an ACTIVE SET UPDATE message to the UE, the RNC measures the item in the best cell that the UE camps on before the handover. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful Soft Handovers with Signaling Only as Initiated by theRNC (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful soft handovers in a cell performed when only signaling exists. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point C as shown in Figure 1. During a soft handover performed when only signaling exists, when the RNC receives an ACTIVE SET UPDATE COMPLETE message from the UE, the RNC measures the item in the best cell that the UE camps on before the handover. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful Soft Handovers Between Neighboring Cells: This measurement item provides the number of successful soft handovers between neighboring cells. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point C, as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC receives an ACTIVE SET UPDATE COMPLETE message from the UE during a soft handover, the RNC measures this item for each pair of source and target cells. Here, the source cells refer to the cells that the UE camps on before the soft handover except the cell whose RL is released in this soft handover. The target cells refer to the cells whose RLs are added and the cell whose RL is released in this soft handover. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of Successful Soft Handovers: This measurement item provides the number of successful soft handovers (including softer handovers). Updated: The measurement is triggered at point C, as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC receives an ACTIVE SET UPDATE COMPLETE message from the UE, which indicates that the soft handover is successful, the RNC measures this item. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of RLs Successfully Added by SRNC on Iur Interface: This measurement item provides the number of RLs successfully added by the SRNC on the Iur interface. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B, as shown in Figure 1. When the SRNC receives a RADIO LINK ADDITION RESPONSE message from the DRNC, the SRNC measures this item separately on different Iur interfaces. Figure1 The measurement is triggered at point B, as shown in Figure 2. When the SRNC receives a RADIO LINK ADDITION FAILURE message from the DRNC and the message indicates that there are successfully established RLs, the SRNC measures this item separately on different Iur interfaces. Figure2 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of RLs Successfully Added on DRNC Iur Interface: This measurement item provides the number of RLs successfully added by a DRNC on the Iur interface. Figure1 The measurement is triggered at point B, as shown in Figure 2. When the DRNC sends a RADIO LINK ADDITION FAILURE message to the SRNC and the message indicates that there are successfully added RLs, this item shall be measured on each Iur interface. Figure2 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of RLs Successfully Reconfigured by SRNC on Iur Interface: This measurement item provides the number of RLs successfully reconfigured by the SRNC. edw_agregation_formula: CASE WHEN $aggreg_net_ri=0 THEN AVG(vs_singlerab_sf4) ELSE SUM(vs_singlerab_sf4) END
comment: Mean Number of Single-RAB UEs Occupy the Codes with Different SpreadingFactors (Cell): The measurement items provide the mean number of single-RAB UEs that occupy the codes with spreading factor (SF) of 4/8/16/32/64/128/256 in a cell. Updated: The RNC takes a sample from the number of single-RAB UEs that occupy the codes with SF of 4/8/16/32/64/128/256 in a cell every five seconds. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC divides the accumulated number of single-RAB UEs by the number of samples to obtain the mean number of single-RAB UEs that occupy the codes with the SF of 4/8/16/32/64/128/256 in a cell. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of RL Additions in Softer Handover (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of RL additions in the softer handover initiated by the RNC in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends an ACTIVE SET UPDATE message to the UE during soft handover. If the handover is a softer handover and a new RL is added, the RNC measures the item in each cell where the new RL is added. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Attempts to Delete RLs in Softer Handover (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of attempts to delete RLs in the softer handover initiated by the RNC in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC sends an ACTIVE SET UPDATE message to the UE. If the handover is a softer handover and an RL is deleted, the RNC measures the item in the cell where the RL is deleted in the soft handover. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of Softer Handovers Initiated by RNC: This measurement item provides the number of softer handovers initiated by the RNC. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B, as shown in Figure 1. During softer handover, when the RNC sends an ACTIVE SET UPDATE message to a UE, the RNC measures this item. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of RL Addition Failures in Softer Handover for Different Causes(Cell): Configuration unsupported Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives an ACTIVE SET UPDATE FAILURE message for the causes described in Table 1from a UE. During the soft handover, if the handover is a softer handover and the RL addition fails, the RNC measures the items in the cell where a new RL is added for different causes during the soft handover . Figure1  (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of RL Addition Failures in Softer Handover for Different Causes(Cell): Incompatible simultaneous reconfiguration Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives an ACTIVE SET UPDATE FAILURE message for the causes described in Table 1from a UE. During the soft handover, if the handover is a softer handover and the RL addition fails, the RNC measures the items in the cell where a new RL is added for different causes during the soft handover . Figure1  (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of RL Addition Failures in Softer Handover for Different Causes(Cell): Invalid configuration Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives an ACTIVE SET UPDATE FAILURE message for the causes described in Table 1from a UE. During the soft handover, if the handover is a softer handover and the RL addition fails, the RNC measures the items in the cell where a new RL is added for different causes during the soft handover . Figure1  (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of RL Addition Failures in Softer Handover for No Response (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of RL addition failures because there is no response from the UE in the softer handover initiated by the RNC. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. The RNC sends an ACTIVE SET UPDATE message to the UE and starts the timer to wait for a response. If it does not receive the response upon expiry of the timer and the handover is a softer handover, the RNC measures the item in the cell where an RL fails to be added during the soft handover. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful RL Additions in Softer Handover (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful RL additions in the softer handover initiated by the RNC in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point C as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives an ACTIVE SET UPDATE COMPLETE message from the UE during soft handover. If the handover is a softer handover and a new RL is added, the RNC measures the item in each cell where the new RL is added. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Number of Successful RL Deletions in Softer Handover (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of successful RL deletions from a cell in the softer handover initiated by the RNC. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point C as shown in Figure 1, when the RNC receives an ACTIVE SET UPDATE COMPLETE message from the UE. If the handover is a softer handover and an RL is deleted, the RNC measures the item in the cell where the RL is deleted in the soft handover. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of Successful Softer Handovers: This measurement item provides the number of successful softer handovers. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point C, as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC receives an ACTIVE SET UPDATE COMPLETE message from the UE, which indicates that the softer handover is successful, the RNC measures this item. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Ratio of Acceptable UL Speech Quality Duration to Conversation Duration(Cell): This measurement item provides the ratio of the time during which the uplink AMR speech quality is acceptable to the total time of conversation in the best cell. Updated: For the best cell, the RNC measures the ratio of the time during which the uplink AMR speech quality (for all the speech users in the cell) is judged as acceptable to the total time of conversation. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

(6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Ratio of Good UL Speech Quality Duration to Conversation Duration (Cell): This measurement item provides the ratio of the time during which the uplink AMR speech quality is good to the total time of conversation in the best cell. Updated: For the best cell, the RNC measures the ratio of the time during which the uplink AMR speech quality (for all the speech users in the cell) is judged as good to the total time of conversation. (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

Percentage of SPU CPU Usage Between Alarm Threshold and Alarm RestoreThreshold: This measurement item provides the percentage of the time when the CPU usage of the SPU subsystem is lower than the alarm threshold but still higher than the alarm restore threshold to the time of the whole measurement period. The item indicates the CPU load of the SPU subsystem in a measurement period. Updated: Samples are taken every second in the specified measurement period. (6810)

Maximum CPU Usage: This measurement item provides the maximum CPU usage of the SPU subsystem in the specified measurement period. The item indicates the CPU usage of the SPU in the measurement period. Updated: Samples are taken every second in the specified measurement period. (6810)

Mean CPU Usage: This measurement item provides the Mean CPU usage of the SPU subsystem in the specified measurement period. The item indicates the CPU usage of the SPU in the measurement period. Updated: Samples are taken every second in the specified measurement period. (6810)

Percentage of SPU CPU Usage over Alarm Threshold: This measurement item provides the percentage of the time when the CPU usage of the SPU subsystem exceeds the alarm threshold to the time of the whole measurement period. The item indicates how the CPU load is over the alarm threshold. Updated: Samples are taken every second in the specified measurement period. (6810)

Maximum DOSMEM Usage: This measurement item provides the maximum DOSMEM usage of the SPU subsystem in the specified measurement period. The item indicates the maximum usage of dynamic memory resource in the measurement period. Updated: Samples are taken every second in the specified measurement period. (6810)

Mean DOSMEM Usage: This measurement item provides the average DOSMEM usage of the SPU subsystem in the specified measurement period. The item indicates the mean usage of dynamic memory resource in the measurement period. Updated: Samples are taken every second in the specified measurement period. (6810)

Maximum MBUF Usage: This measurement item provides the maximum MBUF usage of the SPU subsystem in the specified measurement period. The item indicates the MBUF usage in the measurement period. Updated: Samples are taken every second in the specified measurement period. (6810)

Mean MBUF Usage: This measurement item provides the mean MBUF usage of the SPU subsystem in the specified measurement period. The item indicates the MBUF usage in the measurement period. Updated: Samples are taken every second in the specified measurement period. (6810)

Maximum Usage: This measurement item provides the maximum usage of SPU message packets in the specified measurement period. The item indicates the application of specific memory resource for sending messages in the measurement period. Updated: Samples are taken every second in the specified measurement period. (6810)

Mean Usage of SPU Message Packets: This measurement item provides the mean usage of SPU message packets in the specified measurement period. The item indicates the application of specific memory resource for sending messages in the measurement period. Updated: Samples are taken every second in the specified measurement period. (6810)

RNC Counter: Number of SRNC Relocation Commitment Failures Due to Expiry for Iu ReleaseCommand: PS domain Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. After sending a RELOCATION COMMIT message (The relocation type is UE not Involved) or sending a RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION / RADIO BEARER SETUP / RADIO BEARER RELEASE / TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION / PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message (The relocation type is UE Involved), the SRNC starts the timer to wait for an IU RELEASE COMMAND message. Number of Successful URA Updates due to Change of URA (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of URA UPDATE CONFIRM messages sent from the RNC to the UE after the RNC receives the URA UPDATE message with the cause value of change of URA. In this case, the RNC measures the item in the cell that the UE camps on after the URA update. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of RNC-Originated PAGING TYPE 1 Messages: This measurement item provides the number of PAGING TYPE 1 messages originated by the RNC for triggering the state transition of a UE in CELL_PCH or URA_PCH state. Statistics taken by this item excludes the number of PAGING TYPE 1 messages that the RNC originates for the modification of system information. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. The RNC measures this item when it initiates and sends a PAGING TYPE 1 message to a UE in CELL_PCH or URA_PCH state. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of PAGING TYPE 2 Messages: This measurement item provides the number of PAGING TYPE 2 messages from the RNC to the UE in CELL_FACH or CELL_DCH state. When the RNC receives PAGING messages from the CN, it sends a PAGING TYPE 2 message to the UE if the paged UE is in CELL_FACH or CELL_DCH state. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC receives PAGING messages from the CN, it sends a PAGING TYPE 2 message to the UE in CELL_FACH or CELL_DCH state after receiving a PAGING message from the CN. In this case, the RNC measures this item. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

RNC Counter: Number of Successful Responses to PAGING TYPE 1 Messages: This measurement item provides the number of CELL UPDATE messages from the UEs to the RNC. These messages are taken as successful responses to the PAGING TYPE 1 messages sent by the RNC to the UEs in CELL_PCH or URA_PCH state. After receiving the PAGING TYPE 1 messages, the UEs in CELL_PCH or URA_PCH state send CELL UPDATE messages with the cause of paging response to the RNC. A PAGING TYPE 1 message may be sent to a UE in CELL_PCH or URA_PCH state for the following reasons: The RNC receives a PAGING message from the CN. The UTRAN enables the UE to update system information. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC receives a CELL UPDATE message with the cause of paging response, it measures this item. Figure1 (6810 - 6900 V900R011)

These counters provide the number of successful dynamic channel conversions from DCHs to FACHs or from FACHs to DCHs for R99 service in a cell during the RAB modification procedure and DCCC procedure. The number of successful dynamic channel conversions from DCHs to FACHs is measured in the best cell where the UE camps on before channel conversion. The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in the following figure. In the process of dynamic channel conversion, when the RNC receives the RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE, if the DCH is converted to the FACH, the RNC measures the related counter in the best cell where the UE camps on before channel conversion. If the FACH is converted to the DCH, the RNC measures the related counter in the cell where the UE camps on after channel conversion. (6900 V900R011)

Number of CS Outgoing Inter-RAT Handover Preparation Attempts (Directed retry): This counters provide the number of CS outgoing inter-RAT handover preparations according to different causes. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in the figure. When the RNC sends the CN a RELOCATION REQUIRED message during the CS outgoing inter-RAT handover, the RNC measures these items for each pair of source and target cells according to different causes. Here, the best cell that the UE camps on before the inter-RAT handover is the source cell, and the cell that the UE wants to hand over to is the target cell. (6900 V900R012)

Number of CS Outgoing Inter-RAT Handover Preparation Attempts: This counter provides the number of CS outgoing inter-RAT handover preparations in the originating cell and the target cell. The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in the figure. When the RNC sends the CN a RELOCATION REQUIRED message during the CS outgoing inter-RAT handover, the RNC measures this item for each pair of source and target cells. Here, the best cell that the UE camps on before the inter-RAT handover is the source cell, and the cell that the UE wants to hand over to is the target cell. (6900 V900R012)

Number of Failed CS Outgoing Inter-RAT Handover Preparations (Relocation desirable for radio reasons): This measurement item provides the number of successful CS inter-RAT outgoing handovers between neighboring cells. The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in the figure. When the RNC sends the CN a RELOCATION REQUIRED message during the CS outgoing inter-RAT handover, the RNC measures these items for each pair of source and target cells according to different causes. Here, the best cell that the UE camps on before the inter-RAT handover is the source cell, and the cell that the UE wants to hand over to is the target cell. (6900 V900R012)

Number of Failed CS Outgoing Inter-RAT Handover Preparations (TRELOCalloc expiry):  This counter provides the number of failed CS outgoing inter-RAT handover preparations according to different causes. The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in the figure, when the RNC receives from the CN a RELOCATION PREPARATION FAILURE message after it sends the CN a RELOCATION REQUIRED message during the CS outgoing inter-RAT handover. In this case, the RNC measures this item for each pair of source and target cells according to different causes. Here, the best cell that the UE camps on before the inter-RAT handover is the source cell, and the cell that the UE wants to hand over to is the target cell. (6900 V900R012)

Number of Failed CS Outgoing Inter-RAT Handover Preparations (Relocation Failure in Target CN/RNC or Target System): This counter provides the number of failed CS outgoing inter-RAT handover preparations according to different causes. The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in the figure, when the RNC receives from the CN a RELOCATION PREPARATION FAILURE message after it sends the CN a RELOCATION REQUIRED message during the CS outgoing inter-RAT handover. In this case, the RNC measures this item for each pair of source and target cells according to different causes. Here, the best cell that the UE camps on before the inter-RAT handover is the source cell, and the cell that the UE wants to hand over to is the target cell. (6900 V900R012)

Number of Successful CS Outgoing Inter-RAT Handover Preparations: This counter provides the number of Successful CS outgoing inter-RAT handover preparations. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in the figure, when the RNC receives from the CN a RELOCATION COMMAND message during the CS outgoing inter-RAT handover. In this case, the RNC measures this item for each pair of source and target cells. Here, the best cell that the UE camps on before the inter-RAT handover is the source cell, and the cell that the UE wants to hand over to is the target cell. (6900 V900R012)

RNC Counter: Number of RRC Connection Setups: These two measurement items provide the number of RRC CONNECTION SETUP messages that the RNC sends to the UEs according to different channels for RRC connection setups. VS.RRC.SetupConnEstab: number of RRC CONNECTION SETUP messages that the RNC sends to the UEs. VS.RRC.SetupConnEstab.DCH: number of RRC CONNECTION SETUP messages that the RNC sends to the UEs and through which the RRC connections need to be set up on the DCHs. If the RNC receives a repeated RRC CONNECTINO REQUEST message from a UE, it will send the corresponding RRC CONNECTION SETUP message repeatedly to the UE but measures this item only once. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1. After the RNC receives an RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message from a UE, it initiates the RRC connection setup procedure and then sends an RRC CONNECTION SETUP message to the UE. When related operations on the network side are succeeded, the RNC measures these items. Figure1 (6810)

Number of Connectionless Messages Received by SCCP: This measurement item provides the number of class 0 and class 1 messages received by the SCCP, that is, the number of connectionless messages received by the SCCP. SCCP connectionless messages include UDT, XUDT, LUDT, UDTS, XUDTS and LUDTS. Updated: This measurement is triggered when the SCCP receives a message of class 0 or class 1. (6810)

Number of Connection-Oriented Messages Received by SCCP: This measurement item provides the number of class 2 messages received by the SCCP, that is, the number of connection-oriented messages received by the SCCP. SCCP connection-oriented messages include CR, CC, CREF, RLSD, RLC, DT1 and IT. Updated: This measurement is triggered when the SCCP receives a message of class 2. (6810)

Number of Connectionless Messages Sent by SCCP: This measurement item provides the number of class 0 and class 1 messages sent by the SCCP, that is, the number of connectionless messages sent by the SCCP. SCCP connectionless messages include UDT, XUDT, LUDT, UDTS, XUDTS and LUDTS. Updated: The measurement is triggered when the SCCP sends a message of class 0 or class 1. (6810)

Number of Connection-oriented Messages Sent by SCCP: This measurement item provides the number of class 2 messages sent by the SCCP, that is, the number of connection-oriented messages sent by the SCCP. SCCP connection-oriented messages include CR, CC, CREF, RLSD, RLC, DT1 and IT. Updated: This measurement is triggered when the SCCP sends a message of class 2. (6810)

Number of Normally Released RABs Based on Different Rates (Cell): The measurement items provide the number of normally released RABs that are triggered by the RNC according to different domains in the best cell that belongs to the SRNC. Here, the normal release can be a release initiated by the CN, a release due to 'User Inactivity' initiated by the RNC or a signaling connection release initiated by a UE. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1.When the RNC receives the IU RELEASE COMMAND message, the RNC releases related RABs and sends the IU RELEASE COMPLETE message to the CN. If the release cause is 'Successful Relocation', 'User Inactivity', 'Normal Release' or 'Network Optimization', or before that the RNC sends IU RELEASE REQUEST message to CN due to User Inactivity or the UE initiates a signaling connection release, the RNC measures each item in the best cell the UE camps on. Figure1 The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 2.When the RNC receives the RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message where there are RABs to be released, the RNC releases related RABs and sends the RAB ASSIGNMENT RESPONSE message to the CN. If the release cause is 'Successful Relocation', 'User Inactivity', 'Normal Release' or 'Network Optimization', or before that the RNC sends RAB RELEASE REQUEST message to CN due to User Inactivity, the RNC measures each item in the best cell the UE camps on. Number of Paging Type 1 Messages (Cell): This measurement item provides the number of paging messages of PAGING TYPE 1 sent by the RNC in a cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered when the RNC sends a message of PAGING TYPE 1. (6810)

Number of Successful Responses to PAGING TYPE 1 Messages: This measurement item provides the number of CELL UPDATE messages from the UEs to the RNC. These messages are taken as successful responses to the PAGING TYPE 1 messages sent by the RNC to the UEs in CELL_PCH or URA_PCH state. After receiving the PAGING TYPE 1 messages, the UEs in CELL_PCH or URA_PCH state send CELL UPDATE messages with the cause of 'paging response' to the RNC. A PAGING TYPE 1 message may be sent to a UE in CELL_PCH or URA_PCH state for the following reasons: The RNC receives a PAGING message from the CN. The UTRAN enables the UE to update system information. Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC receives a CELL UPDATE message with the cause of 'paging response', it measures this item. Figure1 (6810)

DL Bit Rate of CS 64 kbit/s Conversational Service (Cell): This measurement item provides the mean DL bit rate of CS 64 bit/s conversational service in a cell. Updated: The RNC measures all DL traffic volume (unit: bit) and duration (unit: ms) of the CS 64 kbit/s conversational service in the SRNC cell of the RLC layer. At the end of the measurement period, the RNC calculates mean bit rate. (6810 - 6900)

Number of High Order Path Remote Errors of FIBER: This measurement item provides the number of the high order path remote errors of the FIBER port in the specified measurement period. The item indicates the status of error cells of the FIBER port in the measurement period. Updated: Samples are taken every five seconds in the specified measurement period. (6810)

Number of Multiplex Section Remote Errors of FIBER: This measurement item provides the number of multiplex section remote errors of the FIBER port in the specified measurement period. The item indicates the status of error cells of the FIBER port in the measurement period. Updated: Samples are taken every five seconds in the specified measurement period. (6810)

DL Rate of CS AMR 4.75 kbit/s Speech Service on Iu Interface: This measurement item provides the actual DL rate of CS AMR 4.75 kbit/s speech service on the Iu interface. Updated: The measurement is triggered when the RNC receives CS AMR 4.75 kbit/s speech service data from the CN domain. (6810)

RNC Counter: Number of PS RABs Requested to Establish: Number of PS RABs requested to establish for streaming services (max DL bit rate more than 384 kbit/s) Updated: The measurement is triggered at point A as shown in Figure 1. When the RNC receives from the SGSN a RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST message about the PS domain, the RNC measures these items according to different types of services. Figure1 (6810 - 6900)

Number of Successfully Established CS RABs (Cell): Number of CS 64 kbit/s service RABs successfully established in the best cell Updated: The measurement is triggered at point B as shown in Figure 1. If the RNC finds that some RABs have been successfully established after receiving a RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE message about the CS domain from the UE, it measures each item according to the types of service and the quantity of RABs successfully established in the best cell. Figure1  (6810 - 6900)

UL BLER of CS 64 kbit/s Real-Time Service on DCH (Cell): This measurement item provides the UL BLER on the dedicated transport channel carrying the CS 64 kbit/s real-time service in the best cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered on the best cell basis when the number of UL data blocks transmitted on the dedicated transport channel carrying the CS 64 kbit/s real-time service reaches the defined sampling window. (6810)

Time Occupancy of Max UL BLER on DCH Carrying CS 64 kbit/s Real-Time Service(Cell): This measurement item provides the ratio of the time taken by the maximum UL BLER on the DCH carrying CS 64 kbit/s real-time service in the best cell. Updated: On the best cell basis, the RNC measures the ratio of the time taken by the maximum UL BLER on the DCH carrying CS 64 kbit/s real-time service to the time taken by the whole outer loop power control. (6810)

UL BLER of PS 8 kbit/s Non-Real-Time Service On RACH (Cell): This measurement item provides the UL BLER on the RACH transport channel carrying the PS 8 kbit/s non-real-time service in the best cell. Updated: The measurement is triggered on the best cell basis when the number of UL data blocks transmitted on the RACH transport channel carrying the PS 8 kbit/s non-real-time service reaches the defined sampling window. (6810 - 6900)

SIR TARGET Measurement of CSRT 14.4 kbit/s Service (Cell): This measurement item provides the ratio of the time when the target SIR of the CSRT 14.4 kbit/s service for all UEs in the best cell reaches the maximum value of the uplink outer loop power control to the total time taken by the uplink outer loop power control in a measurement period. Updated: The RNC measures this item when the target SIR of the CSRT 14.4 kbit/s service for all UEs in the best cell reaches the maximum value and begins to calculate the value of the next target SIR.
